55 char IC::TransitionMarkFromState(IC::State state) {
56  switch (state) {
57  case NO_FEEDBACK:
58  return 'X';
59  case UNINITIALIZED:
60  return '0';
61  case MONOMORPHIC:
62  return '1';
63  case RECOMPUTE_HANDLER:
64  return '^';
65  case POLYMORPHIC:
66  return 'P';
67  case MEGAMORPHIC:
68  return 'N';
69  case MEGADOM:
70  return 'D';
71  case GENERIC:
72  return 'G';
73  }
74  UNREACHABLE();
75 }

79 const char* GetModifier(KeyedAccessLoadMode mode) {
80  switch (mode) {
81  case KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleOOB:
82  return ".OOB";
83  case KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleHoles:
84  return ".HOLES";
85  case KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleOOBAndHoles:
86  return ".OOB+HOLES";
87  case KeyedAccessLoadMode::kInBounds:
88  return "";
89  }
90 }

92 const char* GetModifier(KeyedAccessStoreMode mode) {
93  switch (mode) {
94  case KeyedAccessStoreMode::kHandleCOW:
95  return ".COW";
96  case KeyedAccessStoreMode::kGrowAndHandleCOW:
97  return ".STORE+COW";
98  case KeyedAccessStoreMode::kIgnoreTypedArrayOOB:
99  return ".IGNORE_OOB";
100  case KeyedAccessStoreMode::kInBounds:
101  return "";
102  }
103  UNREACHABLE();
104 }

108 void IC::TraceIC(const char* type, DirectHandle<Object> name) {
109  if (V8_LIKELY(!TracingFlags::is_ic_stats_enabled())) return;
110  State new_state =
111  (state() == NO_FEEDBACK) ? NO_FEEDBACK : nexus()->ic_state();
112  TraceIC(type, name, state(), new_state);
113 }
114 
115 void IC::TraceIC(const char* type, DirectHandle<Object> name, State old_state,
116  State new_state) {
117  if (V8_LIKELY(!TracingFlags::is_ic_stats_enabled())) return;
118 
119  DirectHandle<Map> map = lookup_start_object_map(); // Might be empty.
120 
121  const char* modifier = "";
122  if (state() == NO_FEEDBACK) {
123  modifier = "";
124  } else if (IsKeyedLoadIC()) {
125  KeyedAccessLoadMode mode = nexus()->GetKeyedAccessLoadMode();
126  modifier = GetModifier(mode);
127  } else if (IsKeyedStoreIC() || IsStoreInArrayLiteralIC() ||
128  IsDefineKeyedOwnIC()) {
129  KeyedAccessStoreMode mode = nexus()->GetKeyedAccessStoreMode();
130  modifier = GetModifier(mode);
131  }
132 
133  bool keyed_prefix = is_keyed() && !IsStoreInArrayLiteralIC();
134 
135  if (!(TracingFlags::ic_stats.load(std::memory_order_relaxed) &
136  v8::tracing::TracingCategoryObserver::ENABLED_BY_TRACING)) {
137  LOG(isolate(), ICEvent(type, keyed_prefix, map, name,
138  TransitionMarkFromState(old_state),
139  TransitionMarkFromState(new_state), modifier,
140  slow_stub_reason_));
141  return;
142  }
143 
144  JavaScriptStackFrameIterator it(isolate());
145  JavaScriptFrame* frame = it.frame();
146 
147  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
148  Tagged<JSFunction> function = frame->function();
149 
150  ICStats::instance()->Begin();
151  ICInfo& ic_info = ICStats::instance()->Current();
152  ic_info.type = keyed_prefix ? "Keyed" : "";
153  ic_info.type += type;
154 
155  int code_offset = 0;
156  Tagged<AbstractCode> code;
157  std::tie(code, code_offset) = frame->GetActiveCodeAndOffset();
158  JavaScriptFrame::CollectFunctionAndOffsetForICStats(isolate(), function, code,
159  code_offset);
160 
161  // Reserve enough space for IC transition state, the longest length is 17.
162  ic_info.state.reserve(17);
163  ic_info.state = "(";
164  ic_info.state += TransitionMarkFromState(old_state);
165  ic_info.state += "->";
166  ic_info.state += TransitionMarkFromState(new_state);
167  ic_info.state += modifier;
168  ic_info.state += ")";
169  if (!map.is_null()) {
170  ic_info.map = reinterpret_cast<void*>(map->ptr());
171  ic_info.is_dictionary_map = map->is_dictionary_map();
172  ic_info.number_of_own_descriptors = map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors();
173  ic_info.instance_type = std::to_string(map->instance_type());
174  } else {
175  ic_info.map = nullptr;
176  }
177  // TODO(lpy) Add name as key field in ICStats.
178  ICStats::instance()->End();
179 }

182  FeedbackSlotKind kind)
183  : isolate_(isolate),
184  vector_set_(false),
185  kind_(kind),

188  slow_stub_reason_(nullptr),
189  nexus_(isolate, vector, slot) {
190  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!vector.is_null(), kind_ == nexus_.kind());
191  state_ = (vector.is_null()) ? NO_FEEDBACK : nexus_.ic_state();
192  old_state_ = state_;
193 }

195 static void LookupForRead(LookupIterator* it, bool is_has_property) {
196  for (;; it->Next()) {
197  switch (it->state()) {
198  case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
199  UNREACHABLE();
200  case LookupIterator::JSPROXY:
201  return;
202  case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
203  continue; // Continue to the prototype, if present.
204  case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR: {
205  // If there is a getter, return; otherwise loop to perform the lookup.
206  DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
207  {
208  Tagged<InterceptorInfo> interceptor = holder->GetNamedInterceptor();
209  if (interceptor->has_getter()) {
210  return;
211  }
212  if (is_has_property && interceptor->has_query()) {
213  return;
214  }
215  }
216  continue;
217  }
218  case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
219  // ICs know how to perform access checks on global proxies.
220  if (it->GetHolder<JSObject>().is_identical_to(
221  it->isolate()->global_proxy()) &&
222  !it->isolate()->global_object()->IsDetached(it->isolate())) {
223  continue;
224  }
225  return;
226  case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR:
227  case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
228  case LookupIterator::DATA:
229  case LookupIterator::STRING_LOOKUP_START_OBJECT:
230  case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
231  return;
232  }
233  UNREACHABLE();
234  }
235 }

237 bool IC::ShouldRecomputeHandler(DirectHandle<String> name) {
238  if (!RecomputeHandlerForName(name)) return false;
239 
240  // This is a contextual access, always just update the handler and stay
241  // monomorphic.
242  if (IsGlobalIC()) return true;
243 
244  MaybeObjectDirectHandle maybe_handler =
245  nexus()->FindHandlerForMap(lookup_start_object_map());
246 
247  // The current map wasn't handled yet. There's no reason to stay monomorphic,
248  // *unless* we're moving from a deprecated map to its replacement, or
249  // to a more general elements kind.
250  // TODO(verwaest): Check if the current map is actually what the old map
251  // would transition to.
252  if (maybe_handler.is_null()) {
253  if (!IsJSObjectMap(*lookup_start_object_map())) return false;
254  Tagged<Map> first_map = FirstTargetMap();
255  if (first_map.is_null()) return false;
256  DirectHandle<Map> old_map(first_map, isolate());
257  if (old_map->is_deprecated()) return true;
258  return IsMoreGeneralElementsKindTransition(
259  old_map->elements_kind(), lookup_start_object_map()->elements_kind());
260  }
261 
262  return true;
263 }

265 bool IC::RecomputeHandlerForName(DirectHandle<Object> name) {
266  if (is_keyed()) {
267  // Determine whether the failure is due to a name failure.
268  if (!IsName(*name)) return false;
269  Tagged<Name> stub_name = nexus()->GetName();
270  if (*name != stub_name) return false;
271  }
272 
273  return true;
274 }

276 void IC::UpdateState(DirectHandle<Object> lookup_start_object,
277  DirectHandle<Object> name) {
278  if (state() == NO_FEEDBACK) return;
279  update_lookup_start_object_map(lookup_start_object);
280  if (!IsString(*name)) return;
281  if (state() != MONOMORPHIC && state() != POLYMORPHIC) return;
282  if (IsNullOrUndefined(*lookup_start_object, isolate())) return;
283 
284  // Remove the target from the code cache if it became invalid
285  // because of changes in the prototype chain to avoid hitting it
286  // again.
287  if (ShouldRecomputeHandler(Cast<String>(name))) {
288  MarkRecomputeHandler(name);
289  }
290 }

326 bool MigrateDeprecated(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> object) {
327  if (!IsJSObject(*object)) return false;
328  DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver = Cast<JSObject>(object);
329  if (!receiver->map()->is_deprecated()) return false;
330  JSObject::MigrateInstance(isolate, receiver);
331  return true;
332 }

352 void IC::ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name> name, DirectHandle<Map> map,
353  const MaybeObjectDirectHandle& handler) {

355  nexus()->ConfigureHandlerMode(handler);

365 void IC::ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name> name, MapHandlesSpan maps,
366  MaybeObjectHandles* handlers) {
367  DCHECK(!IsGlobalIC());
368  MapsAndHandlers maps_and_handlers(isolate());
369  maps_and_handlers.reserve(maps.size());
370  DCHECK_EQ(maps.size(), handlers->size());
371  for (size_t i = 0; i < maps.size(); i++) {
372  maps_and_handlers.emplace_back(maps[i], handlers->at(i));
373  }
374  ConfigureVectorState(name, maps_and_handlers);
375 }

387 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> LoadIC::Load(Handle<JSAny> object, Handle<Name> name,
388  bool update_feedback,
389  DirectHandle<JSAny> receiver) {
390  bool use_ic = (state() != NO_FEEDBACK) && v8_flags.use_ic && update_feedback;
391 
392  if (receiver.is_null()) {
393  receiver = object;
394  }
395 
396  // If the object is undefined or null it's illegal to try to get any
397  // of its properties; throw a TypeError in that case.
398  if (IsAnyHas() ? !IsJSReceiver(*object)
399  : IsNullOrUndefined(*object, isolate())) {
400  if (use_ic) {
401  // Ensure the IC state progresses.
402  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_NonReceiver);
403  update_lookup_start_object_map(object);
404  SetCache(name, LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate()));
405  TraceIC("LoadIC", name);
406  }
407 
408  if (IsAnyHas()) {
409  return TypeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidInOperatorUse, object, name);
410  } else {
411  DCHECK(IsNullOrUndefined(*object, isolate()));
412  ErrorUtils::ThrowLoadFromNullOrUndefined(isolate(), object, name);
413  return MaybeDirectHandle<Object>();
414  }
415  }
416 
417  // If we encounter an object with a deprecated map, we want to update the
418  // feedback vector with the migrated map.
419  // Mark ourselves as RECOMPUTE_HANDLER so that we don't turn megamorphic due
420  // to seeing the same map and handler.
421  if (MigrateDeprecated(isolate(), object)) {
422  UpdateState(object, name);
423  }
424 
425  JSObject::MakePrototypesFast(object, kStartAtReceiver, isolate());
426  update_lookup_start_object_map(object);
427 
428  PropertyKey key(isolate(), name);
429  LookupIterator it = LookupIterator(isolate(), receiver, key, object);
430 
431  // Named lookup in the object.
432  LookupForRead(&it, IsAnyHas());
433 
434  if (it.IsFound() || !ShouldThrowReferenceError()) {
435  // Update inline cache and stub cache.
436  if (use_ic) {
437  UpdateCaches(&it);
438  } else if (state() == NO_FEEDBACK) {
439  // Tracing IC stats
440  IsLoadGlobalIC() ? TraceIC("LoadGlobalIC", name)
441  : TraceIC("LoadIC", name);
442  }
443 
444  if (IsAnyHas()) {
445  // Named lookup in the object.
446  Maybe<bool> maybe = JSReceiver::HasProperty(&it);
447  if (maybe.IsNothing()) return MaybeDirectHandle<Object>();
448  return isolate()->factory()->ToBoolean(maybe.FromJust());
449  }
450 
451  // Get the property.
452  DirectHandle<Object> result;
453 
454  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate(), result,
455  Object::GetProperty(&it, IsLoadGlobalIC()));
456  if (it.IsFound()) {
457  return result;
458  } else if (!ShouldThrowReferenceError()) {
459  return result;
460  }
461  }
462  return ReferenceError(name);
463 }

465 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> LoadGlobalIC::Load(Handle<Name> name,
466  bool update_feedback) {
467  Handle<JSGlobalObject> global = isolate()->global_object();
468 
469  if (IsString(*name)) {
470  // Look up in script context table.
471  DirectHandle<String> str_name = Cast<String>(name);
472  DirectHandle<ScriptContextTable> script_contexts(
473  global->native_context()->script_context_table(), isolate());
474 
475  VariableLookupResult lookup_result;
476  if (script_contexts->Lookup(str_name, &lookup_result)) {
477  DirectHandle<Context> script_context(
478  script_contexts->get(lookup_result.context_index), isolate());
479  if (script_context->IsElementTheHole(lookup_result.slot_index)) {
480  // Do not install stubs and stay pre-monomorphic for
481  // uninitialized accesses.
482  THROW_NEW_ERROR(
483  isolate(),
484  NewReferenceError(MessageTemplate::kAccessedUninitializedVariable,
485  name));
486  }
487  bool use_ic =
488  (state() != NO_FEEDBACK) && v8_flags.use_ic && update_feedback;
489  if (use_ic) {
490  // 'const' Variables are mutable if REPL mode is enabled. This disables
491  // compiler inlining for all 'const' variables declared in REPL mode.
492  if (nexus()->ConfigureLexicalVarMode(
493  lookup_result.context_index, lookup_result.slot_index,
494  (IsImmutableLexicalVariableMode(lookup_result.mode) &&
495  !lookup_result.is_repl_mode))) {
496  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadGlobalIC_LoadScriptContextField);
497  } else {
498  // Given combination of indices can't be encoded, so use slow stub.
499  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadGlobalIC_SlowStub);
500  SetCache(name, LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate()));
501  }
502  TraceIC("LoadGlobalIC", name);
503  } else if (state() == NO_FEEDBACK) {
504  TraceIC("LoadGlobalIC", name);
505  }
506  return Context::Get(script_context, lookup_result.slot_index, isolate());
507  }
508  }
509  return LoadIC::Load(global, name, update_feedback);
510 }

514 bool AddOneReceiverMapIfMissing(MapHandles* receiver_maps,
515  Handle<Map> new_receiver_map) {
516  DCHECK(!new_receiver_map.is_null());
517  for (DirectHandle<Map> map : *receiver_maps) {
518  if (!map.is_null() && map.is_identical_to(new_receiver_map)) {
519  return false;
520  }
521  }
522  receiver_maps->push_back(new_receiver_map);
523  return true;
524 }
525 
526 bool AddOneReceiverMapIfMissing(MapsAndHandlers* receiver_maps_and_handlers,
527  Handle<Map> new_receiver_map) {
528  DCHECK(!new_receiver_map.is_null());
529  if (new_receiver_map->is_deprecated()) return false;
530  for (DirectHandle<Map> map : receiver_maps_and_handlers->maps()) {
531  if (!map.is_null() && map.is_identical_to(new_receiver_map)) {
532  return false;
533  }
534  }
535  receiver_maps_and_handlers->emplace_back(new_receiver_map, {});
536  return true;
537 }

552 bool IC::UpdateMegaDOMIC(const MaybeObjectDirectHandle& handler,
553  DirectHandle<Name> name) {
554  if (!v8_flags.mega_dom_ic) return false;
555 
556  // TODO(gsathya): Enable fuzzing once this feature is more stable.
557  if (v8_flags.fuzzing) return false;
558 
559  // TODO(gsathya): Support KeyedLoadIC, StoreIC and KeyedStoreIC.
560  if (!IsLoadIC()) return false;
561 
562  // Check if DOM protector cell is valid.
563  if (!Protectors::IsMegaDOMIntact(isolate())) return false;
564 
565  // Check if current lookup object is an API object
566  DirectHandle<Map> map = lookup_start_object_map();
567  if (!InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSApiObject(map->instance_type())) return false;
568 
569  Handle<Object> accessor_obj;
570  // TODO(gsathya): Check if there are overloads possible for this accessor and
571  // transition only if it isn't possible.
572  if (!accessor().ToHandle(&accessor_obj)) return false;
573 
574  // TODO(gsathya): This is also created in IC::ComputeHandler, find a way to
575  // reuse it here.
576  CallOptimization call_optimization(isolate(), accessor_obj);
577 
578  // Check if accessor is an API function
579  if (!call_optimization.is_simple_api_call()) return false;
580 
581  // Check if accessor requires access checks
582  if (call_optimization.accept_any_receiver()) return false;
583 
584  // Check if accessor requires signature checks
585  if (!call_optimization.requires_signature_check()) return false;
586 
587  // Check if the receiver is the holder
588  CallOptimization::HolderLookup holder_lookup;
589  call_optimization.LookupHolderOfExpectedType(isolate(), map, &holder_lookup);
590  if (holder_lookup != CallOptimization::kHolderIsReceiver) return false;
591 
592  DirectHandle<NativeContext> accessor_context =
593  GetAccessorContext(call_optimization, *map, isolate());
594 
595  DirectHandle<FunctionTemplateInfo> fti;
596  if (IsJSFunction(*accessor_obj)) {
597  fti = direct_handle(
598  Cast<JSFunction>(*accessor_obj)->shared()->api_func_data(), isolate());
599  } else {
600  fti = Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(accessor_obj);
601  }
602 
603  DirectHandle<MegaDomHandler> new_handler =
604  isolate()->factory()->NewMegaDomHandler(
605  MaybeObjectDirectHandle::Weak(fti),
606  MaybeObjectDirectHandle::Weak(accessor_context));
607  nexus()->ConfigureMegaDOM(MaybeObjectDirectHandle(new_handler));
608  return true;
609 }

611 bool IC::UpdateOneMapManyNamesIC(DirectHandle<Name> new_name) {
612 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
613  if (state() != MONOMORPHIC) return false;
614  if (!IsKeyedLoadIC() && !IsKeyedStoreIC()) return false;
615  // For JS objects, using the generic stub is faster. Wasm objects benefit
616  // from collecting a map that the optimizing compiler can use.
617  Tagged<Map> old_map = nexus()->GetFirstMap();
618  if (old_map.is_null() || !IsWasmObjectMap(old_map)) return false;
619  if (old_map != *lookup_start_object_map()) return false;
620  Tagged<Name> old_name = nexus()->GetName();
621  if (old_name.is_null()) return false; // Saw indexed access before.
622  if (old_name == *new_name) return false; // Something else is wrong.
623  DirectHandle<Smi> generic = IsKeyedLoadIC()
624  ? LoadHandler::LoadGeneric(isolate())
625  : StoreHandler::StoreGeneric(isolate());
626  ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name>(), lookup_start_object_map(),
627  generic);
628  return true;
629 #else
630  return false;
631 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
632 }
633 
634 bool IC::UpdatePolymorphicIC(DirectHandle<Name> name,
635  const MaybeObjectDirectHandle& handler) {
636  DCHECK(IsHandler(*handler));
637  if (is_keyed() && state() != RECOMPUTE_HANDLER) {
638  if (nexus()->GetName() != *name) return false;
639  }
640  DirectHandle<Map> map = lookup_start_object_map();
641 
642  MapsAndHandlers maps_and_handlers(isolate());
643  maps_and_handlers.reserve(v8_flags.max_valid_polymorphic_map_count);
644  int deprecated_maps = 0;
645  int handler_to_overwrite = -1;
646 
647  {
648  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
649  int i = 0;
650  for (FeedbackIterator it(nexus()); !it.done(); it.Advance()) {
651  if (it.handler().IsCleared()) continue;
652  MaybeObjectDirectHandle existing_handler(it.handler(), isolate());
653  DirectHandle<Map> existing_map(it.map(), isolate());
654 
655  maps_and_handlers.emplace_back(existing_map, existing_handler);
656 
657  if (existing_map->is_deprecated()) {
658  // Filter out deprecated maps to ensure their instances get migrated.
659  deprecated_maps++;
660  } else if (map.is_identical_to(existing_map)) {
661  // If both map and handler stayed the same (and the name is also the
662  // same as checked above, for keyed accesses), we're not progressing
663  // in the lattice and need to go MEGAMORPHIC instead. There's one
664  // exception to this rule, which is when we're in RECOMPUTE_HANDLER
665  // state, there we allow to migrate to a new handler.
666  if (handler.is_identical_to(existing_handler) &&
667  state() != RECOMPUTE_HANDLER) {
668  return false;
669  }
670 
671  // If the receiver type is already in the polymorphic IC, this indicates
672  // there was a prototoype chain failure. In that case, just overwrite
673  // the handler.
674  handler_to_overwrite = i;
675  } else if (handler_to_overwrite == -1 &&
676  IsTransitionOfMonomorphicTarget(*existing_map, *map)) {
677  handler_to_overwrite = i;
678  }
679 
680  i++;
681  }
682  DCHECK_LE(i, maps_and_handlers.size());
683  }
684 
685  int number_of_maps = static_cast<int>(maps_and_handlers.size());
686  int number_of_valid_maps =
687  number_of_maps - deprecated_maps - (handler_to_overwrite != -1);
688 
689  if (number_of_valid_maps >= v8_flags.max_valid_polymorphic_map_count) {
690  return false;
691  }
692  if (deprecated_maps >= v8_flags.max_valid_polymorphic_map_count) {
693  return false;
694  }
695  if (number_of_maps == 0 && state() != MONOMORPHIC && state() != POLYMORPHIC) {
696  return false;
697  }
698 
699  number_of_valid_maps++;
700  if (number_of_valid_maps == 1) {
701  ConfigureVectorState(name, lookup_start_object_map(), handler);
702  } else {
703  if (is_keyed() && nexus()->GetName() != *name) return false;
704  if (handler_to_overwrite >= 0) {
705  maps_and_handlers.set_handler(handler_to_overwrite, handler);
706  if (!map.is_identical_to(
707  maps_and_handlers.maps()[handler_to_overwrite])) {
708  maps_and_handlers.set_map(handler_to_overwrite, map);
709  }
710  } else {
711  maps_and_handlers.emplace_back(map, handler);
712  }
713 
714  ConfigureVectorState(name, maps_and_handlers);
715  }
716 
717  return true;
718 }
719 
720 void IC::UpdateMonomorphicIC(const MaybeObjectDirectHandle& handler,
721  DirectHandle<Name> name) {
722  DCHECK(IsHandler(*handler));
723  ConfigureVectorState(name, lookup_start_object_map(), handler);
724 }

726 void IC::CopyICToMegamorphicCache(DirectHandle<Name> name) {
727  MapsAndHandlers maps_and_handlers(isolate());
728  nexus()->ExtractMapsAndHandlers(&maps_and_handlers);
729  for (auto [map, handler] : maps_and_handlers) {
730  UpdateMegamorphicCache(map, name, handler);
731  }

734 bool IC::IsTransitionOfMonomorphicTarget(Tagged<Map> source_map,
735  Tagged<Map> target_map) {
736  if (source_map.is_null()) return true;
737  if (target_map.is_null()) return false;
738  if (source_map->is_abandoned_prototype_map()) return false;
739  ElementsKind target_elements_kind = target_map->elements_kind();
740  bool more_general_transition = IsMoreGeneralElementsKindTransition(
741  source_map->elements_kind(), target_elements_kind);
742  Tagged<Map> transitioned_map;
743  if (more_general_transition) {
744  DirectHandle<Map> single_map[1] = {direct_handle(target_map, isolate_)};
745  transitioned_map = source_map->FindElementsKindTransitionedMap(
746  isolate(), single_map, ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous);
747  }
748  return transitioned_map == target_map;
749 }

754 
755 void IC::SetCache(DirectHandle<Name> name, const MaybeObjectHandle& handler) {
756  DCHECK(IsHandler(*handler));
757  // Currently only load and store ICs support non-code handlers.
758  DCHECK(IsAnyLoad() || IsAnyStore() || IsAnyHas());
759  switch (state()) {
760  case NO_FEEDBACK:
761  UNREACHABLE();
762  case UNINITIALIZED:
763  UpdateMonomorphicIC(handler, name);
764  break;
765  case RECOMPUTE_HANDLER:
766  case MONOMORPHIC:
767  if (IsGlobalIC()) {
768  UpdateMonomorphicIC(handler, name);
769  break;
770  }
771  if (UpdateOneMapManyNamesIC(name)) break;
772  [[fallthrough]];
773  case POLYMORPHIC:
774  if (UpdatePolymorphicIC(name, handler)) break;
775  if (UpdateMegaDOMIC(handler, name)) break;
776  if (!is_keyed() || state() == RECOMPUTE_HANDLER) {
777  CopyICToMegamorphicCache(name);
778  }
779  [[fallthrough]];
780  case MEGADOM:
781  ConfigureVectorState(MEGAMORPHIC, name);
782  [[fallthrough]];
783  case MEGAMORPHIC:
784  UpdateMegamorphicCache(lookup_start_object_map(), name, handler);
785  // Indicate that we've handled this case.
786  vector_set_ = true;
787  break;
788  case GENERIC:
789  UNREACHABLE();
790  }
791 }
792 
793 void LoadIC::UpdateCaches(LookupIterator* lookup) {
794  MaybeObjectHandle handler;
795  if (lookup->state() == LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK) {
796  handler = MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate()));
797  } else if (!lookup->IsFound()) {
798  if (lookup->IsPrivateName()) {
799  handler = MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate()));
800  } else {
801  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadNonexistentDH);
802  handler = MaybeObjectHandle(
803  LoadHandler::LoadNonExistent(isolate(), lookup_start_object_map()));
804  }
805  } else if (IsLoadGlobalIC() && lookup->state() == LookupIterator::JSPROXY) {
806  // If there is proxy just install the slow stub since we need to call the
807  // HasProperty trap for global loads. The ProxyGetProperty builtin doesn't
808  // handle this case.
809  handler = MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate()));
810  } else {
811  if (IsLoadGlobalIC()) {
812  if (lookup->TryLookupCachedProperty()) {
813  DCHECK_EQ(LookupIterator::DATA, lookup->state());
814  }
815  if (lookup->state() == LookupIterator::DATA &&
816  lookup->GetReceiver().is_identical_to(lookup->GetHolder<Object>())) {
817  DCHECK(IsJSGlobalObject(*lookup->GetReceiver()));
818  // Now update the cell in the feedback vector.
819  nexus()->ConfigurePropertyCellMode(lookup->GetPropertyCell());
820  TraceIC("LoadGlobalIC", lookup->name());
821  return;
822  }
823  }
824  handler = ComputeHandler(lookup);
825  CHECK(lookup->state() == LookupIterator::STRING_LOOKUP_START_OBJECT ||
826  *lookup->GetHolder<Object>() == *(lookup->lookup_start_object()) ||
827  LoadHandler::CanHandleHolderNotLookupStart(*handler.object()));
828  }
829  // Can't use {lookup->name()} because the LookupIterator might be in
830  // "elements" mode for keys that are strings representing integers above
831  // JSArray::kMaxIndex.
832  SetCache(lookup->GetName(), handler);
833  TraceIC("LoadIC", lookup->GetName());
834 }

856 
857 MaybeObjectHandle LoadIC::ComputeHandler(LookupIterator* lookup) {
858  DirectHandle<Object> receiver = lookup->GetReceiver();
859  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate());
860 
861  DirectHandle<Object> lookup_start_object = lookup->lookup_start_object();
862  // `in` cannot be called on strings, and will always return true for string
863  // wrapper length and function prototypes. The latter two cases are given
864  // LoadHandler::LoadNativeDataProperty below.
865  if (!IsAnyHas() && !lookup->IsElement()) {
866  if (IsString(*lookup_start_object) &&
867  *lookup->name() == roots.length_string()) {
868  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_StringLength);
869  return MaybeObjectHandle(BUILTIN_CODE(isolate(), LoadIC_StringLength));
870  }
871 
872  if (IsStringWrapper(*lookup_start_object) &&
873  *lookup->name() == roots.length_string()) {
874  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_StringWrapperLength);
875  return MaybeObjectHandle(
876  BUILTIN_CODE(isolate(), LoadIC_StringWrapperLength));
877  }
878 
879  // Use specialized code for getting prototype of functions.
880  if (IsJSFunction(*lookup_start_object) &&
881  *lookup->name() == roots.prototype_string() &&
882  !Cast<JSFunction>(*lookup_start_object)
883  ->PrototypeRequiresRuntimeLookup()) {
884  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_FunctionPrototypeStub);
885  return MaybeObjectHandle(
886  BUILTIN_CODE(isolate(), LoadIC_FunctionPrototype));
887  }
888  }
889 
890  DirectHandle<Map> map = lookup_start_object_map();
891  bool holder_is_lookup_start_object =
892  lookup_start_object.is_identical_to(lookup->GetHolder<JSReceiver>());
893 
894  switch (lookup->state()) {
895  case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR: {
896  DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = lookup->GetHolder<JSObject>();
897  Handle<Smi> smi_handler = LoadHandler::LoadInterceptor(isolate());
898 
899  if (holder->GetNamedInterceptor()->non_masking()) {
900  MaybeObjectDirectHandle holder_ref(isolate()->factory()->null_value());
901  if (!holder_is_lookup_start_object || IsLoadGlobalIC()) {
902  holder_ref = MaybeObjectDirectHandle::Weak(holder);
903  }
904  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadNonMaskingInterceptorDH);
905  return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadFullChain(
906  isolate(), map, holder_ref, smi_handler));
907  }
908 
909  if (holder_is_lookup_start_object) {
910  DCHECK(map->has_named_interceptor());
911  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadInterceptorDH);
912  return MaybeObjectHandle(smi_handler);
913  }
914 
915  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadInterceptorFromPrototypeDH);
916  return MaybeObjectHandle(
917  LoadHandler::LoadFromPrototype(isolate(), map, holder, *smi_handler));
918  }
919 
920  case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR: {
921  Handle<JSObject> holder =
922  indirect_handle(lookup->GetHolder<JSObject>(), isolate());
923  // Use simple field loads for some well-known callback properties.
924  // The method will only return true for absolute truths based on the
925  // lookup start object maps.
926  FieldIndex field_index;
927  if (Accessors::IsJSObjectFieldAccessor(isolate(), map, lookup->name(),
928  &field_index)) {
929  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadFieldDH);
930  return MaybeObjectHandle(
931  LoadHandler::LoadField(isolate(), field_index));
932  }
933  if (IsJSModuleNamespace(*holder)) {
934  DirectHandle<ObjectHashTable> exports(
935  Cast<JSModuleNamespace>(holder)->module()->exports(), isolate());
936  InternalIndex entry =
937  exports->FindEntry(isolate(), roots, lookup->name(),
938  Smi::ToInt(Object::GetHash(*lookup->name())));
939  // We found the accessor, so the entry must exist.
940  DCHECK(entry.is_found());
941  int value_index = ObjectHashTable::EntryToValueIndex(entry);
942  Handle<Smi> smi_handler =
943  LoadHandler::LoadModuleExport(isolate(), value_index);
944  if (holder_is_lookup_start_object) {
945  return MaybeObjectHandle(smi_handler);
946  }
947  return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadFromPrototype(
948  isolate(), map, holder, *smi_handler));
949  }
950 
951  DirectHandle<Object> accessors = lookup->GetAccessors();
952  if (IsAccessorPair(*accessors)) {
953  DirectHandle<AccessorPair> accessor_pair =
954  Cast<AccessorPair>(accessors);
955  if (lookup->TryLookupCachedProperty(accessor_pair)) {
956  DCHECK_EQ(LookupIterator::DATA, lookup->state());
957  return MaybeObjectHandle(ComputeHandler(lookup));
958  }
959 
960  Handle<Object> getter(accessor_pair->getter(), isolate());
961  if (!IsCallableJSFunction(*getter) &&
962  !IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*getter)) {
963  // TODO(jgruber): Update counter name.
964  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_SlowStub);
965  return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate()));
966  }
967  set_accessor(getter);
968 
969  if ((IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*getter) &&
970  Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(*getter)->BreakAtEntry(isolate())) ||
971  (IsJSFunction(*getter) &&
972  Cast<JSFunction>(*getter)->shared()->BreakAtEntry(isolate()))) {
973  // Do not install an IC if the api function has a breakpoint.
974  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_SlowStub);
975  return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate()));
976  }
977 
978  Handle<Smi> smi_handler;
979 
980  CallOptimization call_optimization(isolate(), getter);
981  if (call_optimization.is_simple_api_call()) {
982  CallOptimization::HolderLookup holder_lookup;
983  DirectHandle<JSObject> api_holder =
984  call_optimization.LookupHolderOfExpectedType(isolate(), map,
985  &holder_lookup);
986 
987  if (!call_optimization.IsCompatibleReceiverMap(api_holder, holder,
988  holder_lookup) ||
989  !holder->HasFastProperties()) {
990  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_SlowStub);
991  return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate()));
992  }
993 
994  smi_handler = LoadHandler::LoadApiGetter(isolate());
995 
996  DirectHandle<NativeContext> accessor_context =
997  GetAccessorContext(call_optimization, holder->map(), isolate());
998 
999  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadApiGetterFromPrototypeDH);
1000  return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadFromPrototype(
1001  isolate(), map, holder, *smi_handler,
1002  MaybeObjectDirectHandle::Weak(call_optimization.api_call_info()),
1003  MaybeObjectDirectHandle::Weak(accessor_context)));
1004  }
1005 
1006  if (holder->HasFastProperties()) {
1007  DCHECK(IsCallableJSFunction(*getter));
1008  if (holder_is_lookup_start_object) {
1009  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadAccessorDH);
1010  return MaybeObjectHandle::Weak(
1011  indirect_handle(accessor_pair, isolate()));
1012  }
1013  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadAccessorFromPrototypeDH);
1014  return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadFromPrototype(
1015  isolate(), map, holder,
1016  *LoadHandler::LoadAccessorFromPrototype(isolate()),
1017  MaybeObjectDirectHandle::Weak(getter)));
1018  }
1019 
1020  if (IsJSGlobalObject(*holder)) {
1021  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadGlobalFromPrototypeDH);
1022  smi_handler = LoadHandler::LoadGlobal(isolate());
1023  return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadFromPrototype(
1024  isolate(), map, holder, *smi_handler,
1025  MaybeObjectDirectHandle::Weak(lookup->GetPropertyCell())));
1026  } else {
1027  smi_handler = LoadHandler::LoadNormal(isolate());
1028  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadNormalDH);
1029  if (holder_is_lookup_start_object)
1030  return MaybeObjectHandle(smi_handler);
1031  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadNormalFromPrototypeDH);
1032  }
1033 
1034  return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadFromPrototype(
1035  isolate(), map, holder, *smi_handler));
1036  }
1037 
1038  DirectHandle<AccessorInfo> info = Cast<AccessorInfo>(accessors);
1039 
1040  if (info->replace_on_access()) {
1041  set_slow_stub_reason(
1042  "getter needs to be reconfigured to data property");
1043  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_SlowStub);
1044  return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate()));
1045  }
1046 
1047  if (!info->has_getter(isolate()) || !holder->HasFastProperties() ||
1048  (info->is_sloppy() && !IsJSReceiver(*receiver))) {
1049  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_SlowStub);
1050  return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate()));
1051  }
1052 
1053  Handle<Smi> smi_handler = LoadHandler::LoadNativeDataProperty(
1054  isolate(), lookup->GetAccessorIndex());
1055  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadNativeDataPropertyDH);
1056  if (holder_is_lookup_start_object) return MaybeObjectHandle(smi_handler);
1057  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(),
1058  LoadIC_LoadNativeDataPropertyFromPrototypeDH);
1059  return MaybeObjectHandle(
1060  LoadHandler::LoadFromPrototype(isolate(), map, holder, *smi_handler));
1061  }
1062 
1063  case LookupIterator::DATA: {
1064  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> holder = lookup->GetHolder<JSReceiver>();
1065  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, lookup->property_details().kind());
1066  Handle<Smi> smi_handler;
1067  if (lookup->is_dictionary_holder()) {
1068  if (IsJSGlobalObject(*holder, isolate())) {
1069  // TODO(verwaest): Also supporting the global object as receiver is a
1070  // workaround for code that leaks the global object.
1071  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadGlobalDH);
1072  smi_handler = LoadHandler::LoadGlobal(isolate());
1073  return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadFromPrototype(
1074  isolate(), map, holder, *smi_handler,
1075  MaybeObjectDirectHandle::Weak(lookup->GetPropertyCell())));
1076  }
1077  smi_handler = LoadHandler::LoadNormal(isolate());
1078  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadNormalDH);
1079  if (holder_is_lookup_start_object)
1080  return MaybeObjectHandle(smi_handler);
1081  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadNormalFromPrototypeDH);
1082  } else if (lookup->IsElement(*holder)) {
1083  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_SlowStub);
1084  return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate()));
1085  } else {
1086  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyLocation::kField,
1087  lookup->property_details().location());
1088  DCHECK(IsJSObject(*holder, isolate()));
1089  FieldIndex field = lookup->GetFieldIndex();
1090  smi_handler = LoadHandler::LoadField(isolate(), field);
1091  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadFieldDH);
1092  if (holder_is_lookup_start_object)
1093  return MaybeObjectHandle(smi_handler);
1094  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadFieldFromPrototypeDH);
1095  }
1096  if (lookup->constness() == PropertyConstness::kConst &&
1097  !holder_is_lookup_start_object) {
1098  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL,
1099  !lookup->is_dictionary_holder());
1100 
1101  DirectHandle<Object> value = lookup->GetDataValue();
1102 
1103  if (IsThinString(*value)) {
1104  value = direct_handle(Cast<ThinString>(*value)->actual(), isolate());
1105  }
1106 
1107  // Non internalized strings could turn into thin/cons strings
1108  // when internalized. Weak references to thin/cons strings are
1109  // not supported in the GC. If concurrent marking is running
1110  // and the thin/cons string is marked but the actual string is
1111  // not, then the weak reference could be missed.
1112  if (!IsString(*value) ||
1113  (IsString(*value) && IsInternalizedString(*value))) {
1114  MaybeObjectDirectHandle weak_value =
1115  IsSmi(*value) ? MaybeObjectHandle(*value, isolate())
1116  : MaybeObjectHandle::Weak(*value, isolate());
1117 
1118  smi_handler = LoadHandler::LoadConstantFromPrototype(isolate());
1119  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadConstantFromPrototypeDH);
1120  return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadFromPrototype(
1121  isolate(), map, holder, *smi_handler, weak_value));
1122  }
1123  }
1124  return MaybeObjectHandle(
1125  LoadHandler::LoadFromPrototype(isolate(), map, holder, *smi_handler));
1126  }
1127  case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
1128  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), LoadIC_LoadIntegerIndexedExoticDH);
1129  return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadNonExistent(isolate()));
1130 
1131  case LookupIterator::JSPROXY: {
1132  // Private names on JSProxy is currently not supported.
1133  if (lookup->name()->IsPrivate()) {
1134  return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate()));
1135  }
1136  Handle<Smi> smi_handler = LoadHandler::LoadProxy(isolate());
1137  if (holder_is_lookup_start_object) return MaybeObjectHandle(smi_handler);
1138 
1139  DirectHandle<JSProxy> holder_proxy = lookup->GetHolder<JSProxy>();
1140  return MaybeObjectHandle(LoadHandler::LoadFromPrototype(
1141  isolate(), map, holder_proxy, *smi_handler));
1142  }
1143 
1144  case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
1145  case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
1146  case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
1147  case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
1148  case LookupIterator::STRING_LOOKUP_START_OBJECT:
1149  UNREACHABLE();
1150  }
1151 
1152  return MaybeObjectHandle(Handle<InstructionStream>::null());
1153 }

1155 KeyedAccessLoadMode KeyedLoadIC::GetKeyedAccessLoadModeFor(
1156  DirectHandle<Map> receiver_map) const {
1157  const MaybeObjectDirectHandle& handler =
1158  nexus()->FindHandlerForMap(receiver_map);
1159  if (handler.is_null()) return KeyedAccessLoadMode::kInBounds;
1160  return LoadHandler::GetKeyedAccessLoadMode(*handler);

1163 // Returns whether the load mode transition is allowed.
1164 bool AllowedHandlerChange(KeyedAccessLoadMode old_mode,
1165  KeyedAccessLoadMode new_mode) {
1166  // Only allow transitions to allow OOB or allow converting a hole to
1167  // undefined.
1168  using T = std::underlying_type_t<KeyedAccessLoadMode>;
1169  return ((static_cast<T>(old_mode) ^
1170  static_cast<T>(GeneralizeKeyedAccessLoadMode(old_mode, new_mode))) &
1171  0b11) != 0;
1172 }

1174 void KeyedLoadIC::UpdateLoadElement(DirectHandle<HeapObject> receiver,
1175  const KeyedAccessLoadMode new_load_mode) {
1176  Handle<Map> receiver_map(receiver->map(), isolate());
1177  DCHECK(receiver_map->instance_type() !=
1178  JS_PRIMITIVE_WRAPPER_TYPE); // Checked by caller.
1179  MapHandles target_receiver_maps(isolate());
1180  TargetMaps(&target_receiver_maps);
1181 
1182  if (target_receiver_maps.empty()) {
1183  DirectHandle<Object> handler =
1184  LoadElementHandler(receiver_map, new_load_mode);
1185  return ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name>(), receiver_map, handler);
1186  }
1187 
1188  for (DirectHandle<Map> map : target_receiver_maps) {
1189  if (map.is_null()) continue;
1190  if (map->instance_type() == JS_PRIMITIVE_WRAPPER_TYPE) {
1191  set_slow_stub_reason("JSPrimitiveWrapper");
1192  return;
1193  }
1194  if (map->instance_type() == JS_PROXY_TYPE) {
1195  set_slow_stub_reason("JSProxy");
1196  return;
1197  }
1198  }
1199 
1200  // The first time a receiver is seen that is a transitioned version of the
1201  // previous monomorphic receiver type, assume the new ElementsKind is the
1202  // monomorphic type. This benefits global arrays that only transition
1203  // once, and all call sites accessing them are faster if they remain
1204  // monomorphic. If this optimistic assumption is not true, the IC will
1205  // miss again and it will become polymorphic and support both the
1206  // untransitioned and transitioned maps.
1207  if (state() == MONOMORPHIC) {
1208  if ((IsJSObject(*receiver) &&
1209  IsMoreGeneralElementsKindTransition(
1210  target_receiver_maps.at(0)->elements_kind(),
1211  Cast<JSObject>(receiver)->GetElementsKind())) ||
1212  IsWasmObject(*receiver)) {
1213  DirectHandle<Object> handler =
1214  LoadElementHandler(receiver_map, new_load_mode);
1215  return ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name>(), receiver_map, handler);
1216  }
1217  }
1218 
1219  DCHECK(state() != GENERIC);
1220 
1221  // Determine the list of receiver maps that this call site has seen,
1222  // adding the map that was just encountered.
1223  KeyedAccessLoadMode old_load_mode = KeyedAccessLoadMode::kInBounds;
1224  if (!AddOneReceiverMapIfMissing(&target_receiver_maps, receiver_map)) {
1225  old_load_mode = GetKeyedAccessLoadModeFor(receiver_map);
1226  if (!AllowedHandlerChange(old_load_mode, new_load_mode)) {
1227  set_slow_stub_reason("same map added twice");
1228  return;
1229  }
1230  }
1231 
1232  // If the maximum number of receiver maps has been exceeded, use the generic
1233  // version of the IC.
1234  if (static_cast<int>(target_receiver_maps.size()) >
1235  v8_flags.max_valid_polymorphic_map_count) {
1236  set_slow_stub_reason("max polymorph exceeded");
1237  return;
1238  }
1239 
1240  MaybeObjectHandles handlers;
1241  handlers.reserve(target_receiver_maps.size());
1242  KeyedAccessLoadMode load_mode =
1243  GeneralizeKeyedAccessLoadMode(old_load_mode, new_load_mode);
1244  LoadElementPolymorphicHandlers(&target_receiver_maps, &handlers, load_mode);
1245  if (target_receiver_maps.empty()) {
1246  DirectHandle<Object> handler =
1247  LoadElementHandler(receiver_map, new_load_mode);
1248  ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name>(), receiver_map, handler);
1249  } else if (target_receiver_maps.size() == 1) {
1250  ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name>(), target_receiver_maps[0],
1251  handlers[0]);
1252  } else {
1253  ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name>(),
1254  MapHandlesSpan(target_receiver_maps.begin(),
1255  target_receiver_maps.end()),
1256  &handlers);
1257  }
1258 }

1262 bool AllowConvertHoleElementToUndefined(Isolate* isolate,
1263  DirectHandle<Map> receiver_map) {
1264  if (IsJSTypedArrayMap(*receiver_map)) {
1265  // For JSTypedArray we never lookup elements in the prototype chain.
1266  return true;
1267  }
1268 
1269  // For other {receiver}s we need to check the "no elements" protector.
1270  if (Protectors::IsNoElementsIntact(isolate)) {
1271  if (IsStringMap(*receiver_map)) {
1272  return true;
1273  }
1274  if (IsJSObjectMap(*receiver_map)) {
1275  // For other JSObjects (including JSArrays) we can only continue if
1276  // the {receiver}s prototype is either the initial Object.prototype
1277  // or the initial Array.prototype, which are both guarded by the
1278  // "no elements" protector checked above.
1279  DirectHandle<HeapObject> receiver_prototype(receiver_map->prototype(),
1280  isolate);
1281  InstanceType prototype_type = receiver_prototype->map()->instance_type();
1282  if (prototype_type == JS_OBJECT_PROTOTYPE_TYPE ||
1283  (prototype_type == JS_ARRAY_TYPE &&
1284  isolate->IsInCreationContext(
1285  Cast<JSObject>(*receiver_prototype),
1286  Context::INITIAL_ARRAY_PROTOTYPE_INDEX))) {
1287  return true;
1288  }
1289  }
1290  }
1291 
1292  return false;
1293 }
1294 
1295 bool IsOutOfBoundsAccess(DirectHandle<Object> receiver, size_t index) {
1296  size_t length;
1297  if (IsJSArray(*receiver)) {
1298  length = Object::NumberValue(Cast<JSArray>(*receiver)->length());
1299  } else if (IsJSTypedArray(*receiver)) {
1300  length = Cast<JSTypedArray>(*receiver)->GetLength();
1301  } else if (IsJSObject(*receiver)) {
1302  length = Cast<JSObject>(*receiver)->elements()->length();
1303  } else if (IsString(*receiver)) {
1304  length = Cast<String>(*receiver)->length();
1305  } else {
1306  return false;
1307  }
1308  return index >= length;
1309 }

1311 bool AllowReadingHoleElement(ElementsKind elements_kind) {
1312  return IsHoleyElementsKind(elements_kind);
1313 }
1314 
1315 KeyedAccessLoadMode GetNewKeyedLoadMode(Isolate* isolate,
1316  DirectHandle<HeapObject> receiver,
1317  size_t index, bool is_found,
1318  MaybeDirectHandle<Object> result) {
1319  DirectHandle<Map> receiver_map(Cast<HeapObject>(receiver)->map(), isolate);
1320  if (!AllowConvertHoleElementToUndefined(isolate, receiver_map)) {
1321  return KeyedAccessLoadMode::kInBounds;
1322  }
1323 
1324  // Always handle holes when the elements kind is HOLEY_ELEMENTS, since the
1325  // optimizer compilers can not benefit from this information to narrow the
1326  // type. That is, the load type will always just be a generic tagged value.
1327  // This avoid an IC miss if we see a hole.
1328  ElementsKind elements_kind = receiver_map->elements_kind();
1329  bool always_handle_holes = (elements_kind == HOLEY_ELEMENTS);
1330 
1331  // In bound access and did not read a hole.
1332  if (is_found) {
1333 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
1334  // We can encode undefined in HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS, so we always have to
1335  // check for those even if we found a value.
1336  if (elements_kind == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS) {
1337  DirectHandle<Object> result_handle;
1338  if (result.ToHandle(&result_handle)) {
1339  if (Is<Undefined>(result_handle)) {
1340  always_handle_holes = true;
1341  }
1342  }
1343  }
1344 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
1345  return always_handle_holes ? KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleHoles
1346  : KeyedAccessLoadMode::kInBounds;
1347  }
1348 
1349  // OOB access.
1350  bool is_oob_access = IsOutOfBoundsAccess(receiver, index);
1351  if (is_oob_access) {
1352  return always_handle_holes ? KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleOOBAndHoles
1353  : KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleOOB;
1354  }
1355 
1356  // Read a hole.
1357  DCHECK(!is_found && !is_oob_access);
1358  bool handle_hole = AllowReadingHoleElement(elements_kind);
1359  DCHECK_IMPLIES(always_handle_holes, handle_hole);
1360  return handle_hole ? KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleHoles
1361  : KeyedAccessLoadMode::kInBounds;
1362 }
1363 
1364 KeyedAccessLoadMode GetUpdatedLoadModeForMap(Isolate* isolate,
1365  DirectHandle<Map> map,
1366  KeyedAccessLoadMode load_mode) {
1367  // If we are not allowed to convert a hole to undefined, then we should not
1368  // handle OOB nor reading holes.
1369  if (!AllowConvertHoleElementToUndefined(isolate, map)) {
1370  return KeyedAccessLoadMode::kInBounds;
1371  }
1372  // Check if the elements kind allow reading a hole.
1373  bool allow_reading_hole_element =
1374  AllowReadingHoleElement(map->elements_kind());
1375  switch (load_mode) {
1376  case KeyedAccessLoadMode::kInBounds:
1377  case KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleOOB:
1378  return load_mode;
1379  case KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleHoles:
1380  return allow_reading_hole_element ? KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleHoles
1381  : KeyedAccessLoadMode::kInBounds;
1382  case KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleOOBAndHoles:
1383  return allow_reading_hole_element
1384  ? KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleOOBAndHoles
1385  : KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleOOB;
1386  }
1387 }

1391 Handle<Object> KeyedLoadIC::LoadElementHandler(
1392  DirectHandle<Map> receiver_map, KeyedAccessLoadMode new_load_mode,
1393  MaybeDirectHandle<Map> maybe_transition_target) {
1394  // Has a getter interceptor, or is any has and has a query interceptor.
1395  if (receiver_map->has_indexed_interceptor() &&
1396  (receiver_map->GetIndexedInterceptor()->has_getter() ||
1397  (IsAnyHas() && receiver_map->GetIndexedInterceptor()->has_query())) &&
1398  !receiver_map->GetIndexedInterceptor()->non_masking()) {
1399  // TODO(jgruber): Update counter name.
1400  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), KeyedLoadIC_LoadIndexedInterceptorStub);
1401  return IsAnyHas() ? BUILTIN_CODE(isolate(), HasIndexedInterceptorIC)
1402  : BUILTIN_CODE(isolate(), LoadIndexedInterceptorIC);
1403  }
1404 
1405  InstanceType instance_type = receiver_map->instance_type();
1406  if (instance_type < FIRST_NONSTRING_TYPE) {
1407  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), KeyedLoadIC_LoadIndexedStringDH);
1408  if (IsAnyHas()) return LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate());
1409  return LoadHandler::LoadIndexedString(isolate(), new_load_mode);
1410  }
1411  if (instance_type < FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE) {
1412  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), KeyedLoadIC_SlowStub);
1413  return LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate());
1414  }
1415  if (instance_type == JS_PROXY_TYPE) {
1416  return LoadHandler::LoadProxy(isolate());
1417  }
1418 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1419  if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsWasmObject(instance_type)) {
1420  // TODO(jgruber): Update counter name.
1421  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), KeyedLoadIC_SlowStub);
1422  return LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate());
1423  }
1424 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1425 
1426  ElementsKind elements_kind = receiver_map->elements_kind();
1427  if (IsSloppyArgumentsElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
1428  // TODO(jgruber): Update counter name.
1429  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), KeyedLoadIC_KeyedLoadSloppyArgumentsStub);
1430  return IsAnyHas() ? BUILTIN_CODE(isolate(), KeyedHasIC_SloppyArguments)
1431  : BUILTIN_CODE(isolate(), KeyedLoadIC_SloppyArguments);
1432  }
1433  bool is_js_array = instance_type == JS_ARRAY_TYPE;
1434  if (elements_kind == DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS) {
1435  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), KeyedLoadIC_LoadElementDH);
1436  return LoadHandler::LoadElement(isolate(), elements_kind, is_js_array,
1437  new_load_mode);
1438  }
1439  DCHECK(IsFastElementsKind(elements_kind) ||
1440  IsAnyNonextensibleElementsKind(elements_kind) ||
1441  IsTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind));
1442  DCHECK_IMPLIES(
1443  LoadModeHandlesHoles(new_load_mode),
1444  AllowReadingHoleElement(elements_kind) &&
1445  AllowConvertHoleElementToUndefined(isolate(), receiver_map));
1446  DirectHandle<Map> transition_target;
1447  if (is_js_array && maybe_transition_target.ToHandle(&transition_target)) {
1448  DCHECK(IsFastElementsKind(elements_kind));
1449  return LoadHandler::TransitionAndLoadElement(
1450  isolate(), transition_target->elements_kind(), new_load_mode);
1451  }
1452 
1453  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), KeyedLoadIC_LoadElementDH);
1454  return LoadHandler::LoadElement(isolate(), elements_kind, is_js_array,
1455  new_load_mode);
1456 }
1457 
1458 void KeyedLoadIC::LoadElementPolymorphicHandlers(
1459  MapHandles* receiver_maps, MaybeObjectHandles* handlers,
1460  KeyedAccessLoadMode new_load_mode) {
1461  // Filter out deprecated maps to ensure their instances get migrated.
1462  auto new_end = std::remove_if(
1463  receiver_maps->begin(), receiver_maps->end(),
1464  [](const DirectHandle<Map>& map) { return map->is_deprecated(); });
1465  receiver_maps->erase(new_end, receiver_maps->end());
1466 
1467  for (DirectHandle<Map> receiver_map : *receiver_maps) {
1468  Tagged<Map> tmap = receiver_map->FindElementsKindTransitionedMap(
1469  isolate(),
1470  MapHandlesSpan(receiver_maps->begin(), receiver_maps->end()),
1471  ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous);
1472  if (!tmap.is_null()) {
1473  // Mark all stable receiver maps that have elements kind transition map
1474  // among receiver_maps as unstable because the ICs and the optimizing
1475  // compilers may perform an elements kind transition for this kind of
1476  // receivers.
1477  if (receiver_map->is_stable()) {
1478  receiver_map->NotifyLeafMapLayoutChange(isolate());
1479  }
1480  handlers->push_back(MaybeObjectHandle(LoadElementHandler(
1481  receiver_map,
1482  GetUpdatedLoadModeForMap(isolate(), receiver_map, new_load_mode),
1483  handle(tmap, isolate()))));
1484  } else {
1485  handlers->push_back(MaybeObjectHandle(LoadElementHandler(
1486  receiver_map,
1487  GetUpdatedLoadModeForMap(isolate(), receiver_map, new_load_mode))));
1488  }
1489  }
1490 }

1494 enum KeyType { kIntPtr, kName, kBailout };
1495 
1496 // The cases where kIntPtr is returned must match what
1497 // CodeStubAssembler::TryToIntptr can handle!
1498 KeyType TryConvertKey(Handle<Object> key, Isolate* isolate, intptr_t* index_out,
1499  Handle<Name>* name_out) {
1500  if (IsSmi(*key)) {
1501  *index_out = Smi::ToInt(*key);
1502  return kIntPtr;
1503  }
1504  if (IsHeapNumber(*key)) {
1505  double num = Cast<HeapNumber>(*key)->value();
1506  if (!(num >= -kMaxSafeInteger)) return kBailout;
1507  if (num > kMaxSafeInteger) return kBailout;
1508  *index_out = static_cast<intptr_t>(num);
1509  if (*index_out != num) return kBailout;
1510  return kIntPtr;
1511  }
1512  if (IsString(*key)) {
1513  key = isolate->factory()->InternalizeString(Cast<String>(key));
1514  uint32_t maybe_array_index;
1515  if (Cast<String>(*key)->AsArrayIndex(&maybe_array_index)) {
1516  if (maybe_array_index <= INT_MAX) {
1517  *index_out = static_cast<intptr_t>(maybe_array_index);
1518  return kIntPtr;
1519  }
1520  // {key} is a string representation of an array index beyond the range
1521  // that the IC could handle. Don't try to take the named-property path.
1522  return kBailout;
1523  }
1524  *name_out = Cast<String>(key);
1525  return kName;
1526  }
1527  if (IsSymbol(*key)) {
1528  *name_out = Cast<Symbol>(key);
1529  return kName;
1530  }
1531  return kBailout;
1532 }

1534 bool IntPtrKeyToSize(intptr_t index, DirectHandle<HeapObject> receiver,
1535  size_t* out) {
1536  if (index < 0) {
1537  if (IsJSTypedArray(*receiver)) {
1538  // For JSTypedArray receivers, we can support negative keys, which we
1539  // just map to a very large value. This is valid because all OOB accesses
1540  // (negative or positive) are handled the same way, and size_t::max is
1541  // guaranteed to be an OOB access.
1542  *out = std::numeric_limits<size_t>::max();
1543  return true;
1544  }
1545  return false;
1546  }
1547 #if V8_HOST_ARCH_64_BIT
1548  if (index > JSObject::kMaxElementIndex && !IsJSTypedArray(*receiver)) {
1549  return false;
1550  }
1551 #else
1552  // On 32-bit platforms, any intptr_t is less than kMaxElementIndex.
1553  static_assert(
1554  static_cast<double>(std::numeric_limits<decltype(index)>::max()) <=
1555  static_cast<double>(JSObject::kMaxElementIndex));
1556 #endif
1557  *out = static_cast<size_t>(index);
1558  return true;
1559 }

1561 bool CanCache(DirectHandle<Object> receiver, InlineCacheState state) {
1562  if (!v8_flags.use_ic || state == NO_FEEDBACK) return false;
1563  if (!IsJSReceiver(*receiver) && !IsString(*receiver)) return false;
1564  return !IsAccessCheckNeeded(*receiver) && !IsJSPrimitiveWrapper(*receiver);
1565 }

1603 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> KeyedLoadIC::Load(Handle<JSAny> object,
1604  Handle<Object> key) {
1605  if (MigrateDeprecated(isolate(), object)) {
1606  return RuntimeLoad(object, key);
1607  }
1608 
1609  intptr_t maybe_index;
1610  Handle<Name> maybe_name;
1611  KeyType key_type = TryConvertKey(key, isolate(), &maybe_index, &maybe_name);
1612 
1613  if (key_type == kName) return LoadName(object, key, maybe_name);
1614 
1615  bool is_found = false;
1616  MaybeDirectHandle<Object> result = RuntimeLoad(object, key, &is_found);
1617 
1618  size_t index;
1619  if (key_type == kIntPtr && CanCache(object, state()) &&
1620  IntPtrKeyToSize(maybe_index, Cast<HeapObject>(object), &index)) {
1621  DirectHandle<HeapObject> receiver = Cast<HeapObject>(object);
1622  KeyedAccessLoadMode load_mode =
1623  GetNewKeyedLoadMode(isolate(), receiver, index, is_found, result);
1624  UpdateLoadElement(receiver, load_mode);
1625  if (is_vector_set()) {
1626  TraceIC("LoadIC", key);
1627  }
1628  }
1629 
1630  if (vector_needs_update()) {
1631  ConfigureVectorState(MEGAMORPHIC, key);
1632  TraceIC("LoadIC", key);
1633  }
1634 
1635  return result;
1636 }

1638 bool StoreIC::LookupForWrite(LookupIterator* it, DirectHandle<Object> value,
1639  StoreOrigin store_origin) {
1640  // Disable ICs for non-JSObjects for now.
1641  DirectHandle<Object> object = it->GetReceiver();
1642  if (IsJSProxy(*object)) return true;
1643  if (!IsJSObject(*object) && !IsWasmObject(*object)) return false;
1644  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver = Cast<JSReceiver>(object);
1645  DCHECK(!receiver->map()->is_deprecated());
1646 
1647  for (;; it->Next()) {
1648  switch (it->state()) {
1649  case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
1650  UNREACHABLE();
1651  case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
1652  continue; // Continue to the prototype, if present.
1653  case LookupIterator::JSPROXY:
1654  return true;
1655  case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR: {
1656  DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
1657  Tagged<InterceptorInfo> info = holder->GetNamedInterceptor();
1658  if (it->HolderIsReceiverOrHiddenPrototype() || info->has_getter() ||
1659  info->has_query()) {
1660  return true;
1661  }
1662  continue;
1663  }
1664  case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
1665  if (IsAccessCheckNeeded(*it->GetHolder<JSObject>())) return false;
1666  continue;
1667  case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR:
1668  return !it->IsReadOnly();
1669  case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
1670  return false;
1671  case LookupIterator::DATA: {
1672  if (it->IsReadOnly()) return false;
1673  if (IsAnyDefineOwn() && it->property_attributes() != NONE) {
1674  // IC doesn't support reconfiguration of property attributes,
1675  // so just bail out to the slow handler.
1676  return false;
1677  }
1678  DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
1679  if (receiver.is_identical_to(holder)) {
1680  it->PrepareForDataProperty(value);
1681  // The previous receiver map might just have been deprecated,
1682  // so reload it.
1683  update_lookup_start_object_map(receiver);
1684  return true;
1685  }
1686 
1687  // Receiver != holder.
1688  if (IsJSGlobalProxy(*receiver)) {
1689  PrototypeIterator iter(isolate(), receiver);
1690  return it->GetHolder<Object>().is_identical_to(
1691  PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent(iter));
1692  }
1693 
1694  if (it->HolderIsReceiverOrHiddenPrototype()) return false;
1695 
1696  if (it->ExtendingNonExtensible(receiver)) return false;
1697  it->PrepareTransitionToDataProperty(receiver, value, NONE,
1698  store_origin);
1699  return it->IsCacheableTransition();
1700  }
1701  case LookupIterator::STRING_LOOKUP_START_OBJECT:
1702  UNREACHABLE();
1703 
1704  case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
1705  // If we are in StoreGlobal then check if we should throw on
1706  // non-existent properties.
1707  if (IsStoreGlobalIC() &&
1708  (GetShouldThrow(it->isolate(), Nothing<ShouldThrow>()) ==
1709  ShouldThrow::kThrowOnError)) {
1710  // ICs typically does the store in two steps: prepare receiver for the
1711  // transition followed by the actual store. For global objects we
1712  // create a property cell when preparing for transition and install
1713  // this cell in the handler. In strict mode, we throw and never
1714  // initialize this property cell. The IC handler assumes that the
1715  // property cell it is holding is for a property that is existing.
1716  // This case violates this assumption. If we happen to invalidate this
1717  // property cell later, it leads to incorrect behaviour. For now just
1718  // use a slow stub and don't install the property cell for these
1719  // cases. Hopefully these cases are not frequent enough to impact
1720  // performance.
1721  //
1722  // TODO(mythria): If we find this to be happening often, we could
1723  // install a new kind of handler for non-existent properties. These
1724  // handlers can then miss to runtime if the value is not hole (i.e.
1725  // cell got invalidated) and handle these stores correctly.
1726  return false;
1727  }
1728  receiver = it->GetStoreTarget<JSReceiver>();
1729  if (it->ExtendingNonExtensible(receiver)) return false;
1730  it->PrepareTransitionToDataProperty(receiver, value, NONE,
1731  store_origin);
1732  return it->IsCacheableTransition();
1733  }
1734  UNREACHABLE();
1735  }
1736 }
1737 
1738 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> StoreGlobalIC::Store(Handle<Name> name,
1739  DirectHandle<Object> value) {
1740  DCHECK(IsString(*name));
1741 
1742  // Look up in script context table.
1743  DirectHandle<String> str_name = Cast<String>(name);
1744  Handle<JSGlobalObject> global = isolate()->global_object();
1745  DirectHandle<ScriptContextTable> script_contexts(
1746  global->native_context()->script_context_table(), isolate());
1747 
1748  VariableLookupResult lookup_result;
1749  if (script_contexts->Lookup(str_name, &lookup_result)) {
1750  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1751  DisableGCMole no_gcmole;
1752  Tagged<Context> script_context =
1753  script_contexts->get(lookup_result.context_index);
1754  if (IsImmutableLexicalVariableMode(lookup_result.mode)) {
1755  AllowGarbageCollection yes_gc;
1756  return TypeError(MessageTemplate::kConstAssign, global, name);
1757  }
1758 
1759  if (script_context->IsElementTheHole(lookup_result.slot_index)) {
1760  // Do not install stubs and stay pre-monomorphic for uninitialized
1761  // accesses.
1762  AllowGarbageCollection yes_gc;
1763  THROW_NEW_ERROR(
1764  isolate(),
1765  NewReferenceError(MessageTemplate::kAccessedUninitializedVariable,
1766  name));
1767  }
1768 
1769  bool use_ic = (state() != NO_FEEDBACK) && v8_flags.use_ic;
1770  if (use_ic) {
1771  if (nexus()->ConfigureLexicalVarMode(
1772  lookup_result.context_index, lookup_result.slot_index,
1773  IsImmutableLexicalVariableMode(lookup_result.mode))) {
1774  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreGlobalIC_StoreScriptContextField);
1775  } else {
1776  // Given combination of indices can't be encoded, so use slow stub.
1777  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreGlobalIC_SlowStub);
1778  SetCache(name, StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
1779  }
1780  TraceIC("StoreGlobalIC", name);
1781  } else if (state() == NO_FEEDBACK) {
1782  TraceIC("StoreGlobalIC", name);
1783  }
1784  AllowGarbageCollection yes_gc;
1785  Context::Set(handle(script_context, isolate()), lookup_result.slot_index,
1786  value, isolate());
1787  return value;
1788  }
1789 
1790  return StoreIC::Store(global, name, value);
1791 }

1793 namespace {
1794 Maybe<bool> DefineOwnDataProperty(LookupIterator* it,
1795  LookupIterator::State original_state,
1796  DirectHandle<JSAny> value,
1797  Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw,
1798  StoreOrigin store_origin) {
1799  // It should not be possible to call DefineOwnDataProperty in a
1800  // contextual store (indicated by IsJSGlobalObject()).
1801  DCHECK(!IsJSGlobalObject(*it->GetReceiver(), it->isolate()));
1802 
1803  // Handle special cases that can't be handled by
1804  // DefineOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes first.
1805  switch (it->state()) {
1806  case LookupIterator::JSPROXY: {
1807  PropertyDescriptor new_desc;
1808  new_desc.set_value(value);
1809  new_desc.set_writable(true);
1810  new_desc.set_enumerable(true);
1811  new_desc.set_configurable(true);
1812  DCHECK_EQ(original_state, LookupIterator::JSPROXY);
1813  // TODO(joyee): this will start the lookup again. Ideally we should
1814  // implement something that reuses the existing LookupIterator.
1815  return JSProxy::DefineOwnProperty(it->isolate(), it->GetHolder<JSProxy>(),
1816  it->GetName(), &new_desc, should_throw);
1817  }
1818  case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
1819  RETURN_FAILURE(it->isolate(), kThrowOnError,
1820  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kWasmObjectsAreOpaque));
1821  // When lazy feedback is disabled, the original state could be different
1822  // while the object is already prepared for TRANSITION.
1823  case LookupIterator::TRANSITION: {
1824  switch (original_state) {
1825  case LookupIterator::JSPROXY:
1826  case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
1827  case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
1828  case LookupIterator::DATA:
1829  case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR:
1830  case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR:
1831  case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
1832  case LookupIterator::STRING_LOOKUP_START_OBJECT:
1833  UNREACHABLE();
1834  case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK: {
1835  DCHECK(!IsAccessCheckNeeded(*it->GetHolder<JSObject>()));
1836  [[fallthrough]];
1837  }
1838  case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
1839  return Object::AddDataProperty(it, value, NONE,
1840  Nothing<ShouldThrow>(), store_origin,
1841  EnforceDefineSemantics::kDefine);
1842  }
1843  }
1844  case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
1845  case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
1846  case LookupIterator::DATA:
1847  case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR:
1848  case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR:
1849  case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
1850  break;
1851  case LookupIterator::STRING_LOOKUP_START_OBJECT:
1852  UNREACHABLE();
1853  }
1854 
1855  // We need to restart to handle interceptors properly.
1856  it->Restart();
1857 
1858  return JSObject::DefineOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes(
1859  it, value, NONE, should_throw, JSObject::DONT_FORCE_FIELD,
1860  EnforceDefineSemantics::kDefine, store_origin);
1861 }
