1863 
1864 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> StoreIC::Store(Handle<JSAny> object,
1865  Handle<Name> name,
1866  DirectHandle<Object> value,
1867  StoreOrigin store_origin) {
1868  // TODO(verwaest): Let SetProperty do the migration, since storing a property
1869  // might deprecate the current map again, if value does not fit.
1870  if (MigrateDeprecated(isolate(), object)) {
1871  // KeyedStoreIC should handle DefineKeyedOwnIC with deprecated maps directly
1872  // instead of reusing this method.
1873  DCHECK(!IsDefineKeyedOwnIC());
1874  DCHECK(!name->IsPrivateName());
1875 
1876  PropertyKey key(isolate(), name);
1877  if (IsDefineNamedOwnIC()) {
1878  MAYBE_RETURN_NULL(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(
1879  isolate(), object, key, value, Nothing<ShouldThrow>()));
1880  } else {
1881  LookupIterator it(isolate(), object, key, LookupIterator::DEFAULT);
1882  MAYBE_RETURN_NULL(Object::SetProperty(&it, value, StoreOrigin::kNamed));
1883  }
1884  return value;
1885  }
1886 
1887  bool use_ic = (state() != NO_FEEDBACK) && v8_flags.use_ic;
1888  // If the object is undefined or null it's illegal to try to set any
1889  // properties on it; throw a TypeError in that case.
1890  if (IsNullOrUndefined(*object, isolate())) {
1891  if (use_ic) {
1892  // Ensure the IC state progresses.
1893  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_NonReceiver);
1894  update_lookup_start_object_map(object);
1895  SetCache(name, StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
1896  TraceIC("StoreIC", name);
1897  }
1898  return TypeError(MessageTemplate::kNonObjectPropertyStoreWithProperty, name,
1899  object);
1900  }
1901 
1902  JSObject::MakePrototypesFast(object, kStartAtPrototype, isolate());
1903  PropertyKey key(isolate(), name);
1904  LookupIterator it(
1905  isolate(), object, key,
1906  IsAnyDefineOwn() ? LookupIterator::OWN : LookupIterator::DEFAULT);
1907 
1908  if (name->IsPrivate()) {
1909  if (name->IsPrivateName()) {
1910  DCHECK(!IsDefineNamedOwnIC());
1911  Maybe<bool> can_store =
1912  JSReceiver::CheckPrivateNameStore(&it, IsDefineKeyedOwnIC());
1913  MAYBE_RETURN_NULL(can_store);
1914  if (!can_store.FromJust()) {
1915  return isolate()->factory()->undefined_value();
1916  }
1917  }
1918 
1919  // IC handling of private fields/symbols stores on JSProxy is not
1920  // supported.
1921  if (IsJSProxy(*object)) {
1922  use_ic = false;
1923  }
1924  }
1925 
1926  // For IsAnyDefineOwn(), we can't simply do CreateDataProperty below
1927  // because we need to check the attributes before UpdateCaches updates
1928  // the state of the LookupIterator.
1929  LookupIterator::State original_state = it.state();
1930  // We'll defer the check for JSProxy and objects with named interceptors,
1931  // because the defineProperty traps need to be called first if they are
1932  // present. We can also skip this for private names since they are not
1933  // bound by configurability or extensibility checks, and errors would've
1934  // been thrown if the private field already exists in the object.
1935  if (IsAnyDefineOwn() && !name->IsPrivateName() && IsJSObject(*object) &&
1936  !Cast<JSObject>(object)->HasNamedInterceptor()) {
1937  Maybe<bool> can_define = JSObject::CheckIfCanDefineAsConfigurable(
1938  isolate(), &it, value, Nothing<ShouldThrow>());
1939  MAYBE_RETURN_NULL(can_define);
1940  if (!can_define.FromJust()) {
1941  return isolate()->factory()->undefined_value();
1942  }
1943  // Restart the lookup iterator updated by CheckIfCanDefineAsConfigurable()
1944  // for UpdateCaches() to handle access checks.
1945  if (use_ic && IsAccessCheckNeeded(*object)) {
1946  it.Restart();
1947  }
1948  }
1949 
1950  if (use_ic) {
1951  UpdateCaches(&it, value, store_origin);
1952  } else if (state() == NO_FEEDBACK) {
1953  // Tracing IC Stats for No Feedback State.
1954  IsStoreGlobalIC() ? TraceIC("StoreGlobalIC", name)
1955  : TraceIC("StoreIC", name);
1956  }
1957 
1958  // TODO(v8:12548): refactor DefinedNamedOwnIC and SetNamedIC as subclasses
1959  // of StoreIC so their logic doesn't get mixed here.
1960  // ES #sec-definefield
1961  // ES #sec-runtime-semantics-propertydefinitionevaluation
1962  // IsAnyDefineOwn() can be true when this method is reused by KeyedStoreIC.
1963  if (IsAnyDefineOwn()) {
1964  if (name->IsPrivateName()) {
1965  // We should define private fields without triggering traps or checking
1966  // extensibility.
1967  MAYBE_RETURN_NULL(
1968  JSReceiver::AddPrivateField(&it, value, Nothing<ShouldThrow>()));
1969  } else {
1970  MAYBE_RETURN_NULL(
1971  DefineOwnDataProperty(&it, original_state, Cast<JSAny>(value),
1972  Nothing<ShouldThrow>(), store_origin));
1973  }
1974  } else {
1975  MAYBE_RETURN_NULL(Object::SetProperty(&it, value, store_origin));
1976  }
1977  return value;
1978 }
1979 
1980 void StoreIC::UpdateCaches(LookupIterator* lookup, DirectHandle<Object> value,
1981  StoreOrigin store_origin) {
1982  MaybeObjectHandle handler;
1983  if (LookupForWrite(lookup, value, store_origin)) {
1984  if (IsStoreGlobalIC()) {
1985  if (lookup->state() == LookupIterator::DATA &&
1986  lookup->GetReceiver().is_identical_to(lookup->GetHolder<Object>())) {
1987  DCHECK(IsJSGlobalObject(*lookup->GetReceiver()));
1988  // Now update the cell in the feedback vector.
1989  nexus()->ConfigurePropertyCellMode(lookup->GetPropertyCell());
1990  TraceIC("StoreGlobalIC", lookup->GetName());
1991  return;
1992  }
1993  }
1994  handler = ComputeHandler(lookup);
1995  } else {
1996  set_slow_stub_reason("LookupForWrite said 'false'");
1997  handler = MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
1998  }
1999  // Can't use {lookup->name()} because the LookupIterator might be in
2000  // "elements" mode for keys that are strings representing integers above
2001  // JSArray::kMaxIndex.
2002  SetCache(lookup->GetName(), handler);
2003  TraceIC("StoreIC", lookup->GetName());
2004 }
2005 
2006 MaybeObjectHandle StoreIC::ComputeHandler(LookupIterator* lookup) {
2007  switch (lookup->state()) {
2008  case LookupIterator::TRANSITION: {
2009  DirectHandle<JSObject> store_target = lookup->GetStoreTarget<JSObject>();
2010  if (IsJSGlobalObject(*store_target)) {
2011  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_StoreGlobalTransitionDH);
2012 
2013  if (IsJSGlobalObject(*lookup_start_object_map())) {
2014  DCHECK(IsStoreGlobalIC());
2015 #ifdef DEBUG
2016  DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = lookup->GetHolder<JSObject>();
2017  DCHECK_EQ(*lookup->GetReceiver(), *holder);
2018  DCHECK_EQ(*store_target, *holder);
2019 #endif
2020  return StoreHandler::StoreGlobal(
2021  indirect_handle(lookup->transition_cell(), isolate()));
2022  }
2023  if (IsDefineKeyedOwnIC()) {
2024  // Private field can't be deleted from this global object and can't
2025  // be overwritten, so install slow handler in order to make store IC
2026  // throw if a private name already exists.
2027  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_SlowStub);
2028  return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2029  }
2030 
2031  DirectHandle<Smi> smi_handler =
2032  StoreHandler::StoreGlobalProxy(isolate());
2033  Handle<Object> handler = StoreHandler::StoreThroughPrototype(
2034  isolate(), lookup_start_object_map(), store_target, *smi_handler,
2035  MaybeObjectDirectHandle::Weak(lookup->transition_cell()));
2036  return MaybeObjectHandle(handler);
2037  }
2038  // Dictionary-to-fast transitions are not expected and not supported.
2039  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!lookup->transition_map()->is_dictionary_map(),
2040  !lookup_start_object_map()->is_dictionary_map());
2041 
2042  DCHECK(lookup->IsCacheableTransition());
2043  if (IsAnyDefineOwn()) {
2044  return StoreHandler::StoreOwnTransition(
2045  isolate(), indirect_handle(lookup->transition_map(), isolate()));
2046  }
2047  return StoreHandler::StoreTransition(
2048  isolate(), indirect_handle(lookup->transition_map(), isolate()));
2049  }
2050 
2051  case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR: {
2052  DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = lookup->GetHolder<JSObject>();
2053  Tagged<InterceptorInfo> info = holder->GetNamedInterceptor();
2054 
2055  // If the interceptor is on the receiver...
2056  if (lookup->HolderIsReceiverOrHiddenPrototype() && !info->non_masking()) {
2057  // ...return a store interceptor Smi handler if there is a setter
2058  // interceptor and it's not DefineNamedOwnIC or DefineKeyedOwnIC
2059  // (which should call the definer)...
2060  if (info->has_setter() && !IsAnyDefineOwn()) {
2061  return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreInterceptor(isolate()));
2062  }
2063  // ...otherwise return a slow-case Smi handler, which invokes the
2064  // definer for DefineNamedOwnIC.
2065  return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2066  }
2067 
2068  // If the interceptor is a getter/query interceptor on the prototype
2069  // chain, return an invalidatable slow handler so it can turn fast if the
2070  // interceptor is masked by a regular property later.
2071  DCHECK(info->has_getter() || info->has_query());
2072  Handle<Object> handler = StoreHandler::StoreThroughPrototype(
2073  isolate(), lookup_start_object_map(), holder,
2074  *StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2075  return MaybeObjectHandle(handler);
2076  }
2077 
2078  case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR: {
2079  // This is currently guaranteed by checks in StoreIC::Store.
2080  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver =
2081  Cast<JSReceiver>(lookup->GetReceiver());
2082  Handle<JSObject> holder =
2083  indirect_handle(lookup->GetHolder<JSObject>(), isolate());
2084  DCHECK(!IsAccessCheckNeeded(*receiver) || lookup->name()->IsPrivate());
2085 
2086  if (IsAnyDefineOwn()) {
2087  set_slow_stub_reason("define own with existing accessor");
2088  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_SlowStub);
2089  return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2090  }
2091  if (!holder->HasFastProperties()) {
2092  set_slow_stub_reason("accessor on slow map");
2093  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_SlowStub);
2094  MaybeObjectHandle handler =
2095  MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2096  return handler;
2097  }
2098  DirectHandle<Object> accessors = lookup->GetAccessors();
2099  if (IsAccessorInfo(*accessors)) {
2100  DirectHandle<AccessorInfo> info = Cast<AccessorInfo>(accessors);
2101  if (!info->has_setter(isolate())) {
2102  set_slow_stub_reason("setter == kNullAddress");
2103  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_SlowStub);
2104  return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2105  }
2106  if (!lookup->HolderIsReceiverOrHiddenPrototype()) {
2107  set_slow_stub_reason("native data property in prototype chain");
2108  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_SlowStub);
2109  return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2110  }
2111 
2112  Handle<Smi> smi_handler = StoreHandler::StoreNativeDataProperty(
2113  isolate(), lookup->GetAccessorIndex());
2114  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_StoreNativeDataPropertyDH);
2115  if (receiver.is_identical_to(holder)) {
2116  return MaybeObjectHandle(smi_handler);
2117  }
2118  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(),
2119  StoreIC_StoreNativeDataPropertyOnPrototypeDH);
2120  return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreThroughPrototype(
2121  isolate(), lookup_start_object_map(), holder, *smi_handler));
2122 
2123  } else if (IsAccessorPair(*accessors)) {
2124  DirectHandle<AccessorPair> accessor_pair =
2125  Cast<AccessorPair>(accessors);
2126  Handle<Object> setter(accessor_pair->setter(), isolate());
2127  if (!IsCallableJSFunction(*setter) &&
2128  !IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*setter)) {
2129  set_slow_stub_reason("setter not a function");
2130  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_SlowStub);
2131  return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2132  }
2133 
2134  if ((IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*setter) &&
2135  Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(*setter)->BreakAtEntry(isolate())) ||
2136  (IsJSFunction(*setter) &&
2137  Cast<JSFunction>(*setter)->shared()->BreakAtEntry(isolate()))) {
2138  // Do not install an IC if the api function has a breakpoint.
2139  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_SlowStub);
2140  return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2141  }
2142 
2143  CallOptimization call_optimization(isolate(), setter);
2144  if (call_optimization.is_simple_api_call()) {
2145  CallOptimization::HolderLookup holder_lookup;
2146  DirectHandle<JSObject> api_holder =
2147  call_optimization.LookupHolderOfExpectedType(
2148  isolate(), lookup_start_object_map(), &holder_lookup);
2149  if (call_optimization.IsCompatibleReceiverMap(api_holder, holder,
2150  holder_lookup)) {
2151  DirectHandle<Smi> smi_handler =
2152  StoreHandler::StoreApiSetter(isolate());
2153 
2154  DirectHandle<NativeContext> accessor_context =
2155  GetAccessorContext(call_optimization, holder->map(), isolate());
2156 
2157  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_StoreApiSetterOnPrototypeDH);
2158  return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreThroughPrototype(
2159  isolate(), lookup_start_object_map(), holder, *smi_handler,
2160  MaybeObjectDirectHandle::Weak(
2161  call_optimization.api_call_info()),
2162  MaybeObjectDirectHandle::Weak(accessor_context)));
2163  }
2164  set_slow_stub_reason("incompatible receiver");
2165  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_SlowStub);
2166  return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2167  } else if (IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*setter)) {
2168  set_slow_stub_reason("setter non-simple template");
2169  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_SlowStub);
2170  return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2171  }
2172 
2173  DCHECK(IsCallableJSFunction(*setter));
2174  if (receiver.is_identical_to(holder)) {
2175  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_StoreAccessorDH);
2176  return MaybeObjectHandle::Weak(
2177  indirect_handle(accessor_pair, isolate()));
2178  }
2179  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_StoreAccessorOnPrototypeDH);
2180 
2181  return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreThroughPrototype(
2182  isolate(), lookup_start_object_map(), holder,
2183  *StoreHandler::StoreAccessorFromPrototype(isolate()),
2184  MaybeObjectDirectHandle::Weak(setter)));
2185  }
2186  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_SlowStub);
2187  return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2188  }
2189 
2190  case LookupIterator::DATA: {
2191  // This is currently guaranteed by checks in StoreIC::Store.
2192  DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver = Cast<JSObject>(lookup->GetReceiver());
2193  USE(receiver);
2194  DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = lookup->GetHolder<JSObject>();
2195  DCHECK(!IsAccessCheckNeeded(*receiver) || lookup->name()->IsPrivate());
2196 
2197  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, lookup->property_details().kind());
2198  if (lookup->is_dictionary_holder()) {
2199  if (IsJSGlobalObject(*holder)) {
2200  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_StoreGlobalDH);
2201  return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreGlobal(
2202  indirect_handle(lookup->GetPropertyCell(), isolate())));
2203  }
2204  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_StoreNormalDH);
2205  DCHECK(holder.is_identical_to(receiver));
2206  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL,
2207  lookup->constness() == PropertyConstness::kMutable);
2208 
2209  Handle<Smi> handler = StoreHandler::StoreNormal(isolate());
2210  return MaybeObjectHandle(handler);
2211  }
2212 
2213  // -------------- Elements (for TypedArrays) -------------
2214  if (lookup->IsElement(*holder)) {
2215  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_SlowStub);
2216  return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2217  }
2218 
2219  // -------------- Fields --------------
2220  if (lookup->property_details().location() == PropertyLocation::kField) {
2221  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_StoreFieldDH);
2222  int descriptor = lookup->GetFieldDescriptorIndex();
2223  FieldIndex index = lookup->GetFieldIndex();
2224  if (V8_UNLIKELY(IsJSSharedStruct(*holder))) {
2225  return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSharedStructField(
2226  isolate(), descriptor, index, lookup->representation()));
2227  }
2228  PropertyConstness constness = lookup->constness();
2229  if (constness == PropertyConstness::kConst &&
2230  IsDefineNamedOwnICKind(nexus()->kind())) {
2231  // DefineNamedOwnICs are used for initializing object literals
2232  // therefore we must store the value unconditionally even to
2233  // VariableMode::kConst fields.
2234  constness = PropertyConstness::kMutable;
2235  }
2236  return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreField(
2237  isolate(), descriptor, index, constness, lookup->representation()));
2238  }
2239 
2240  // -------------- Constant properties --------------
2241  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyLocation::kDescriptor,
2242  lookup->property_details().location());
2243  set_slow_stub_reason("constant property");
2244  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_SlowStub);
2245  return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2246  }
2247  case LookupIterator::JSPROXY: {
2248  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver =
2249  Cast<JSReceiver>(lookup->GetReceiver());
2250  Handle<JSProxy> holder =
2251  indirect_handle(lookup->GetHolder<JSProxy>(), isolate());
2252 
2253  // IsDefineNamedOwnIC() is true when we are defining public fields on a
2254  // Proxy. IsDefineKeyedOwnIC() is true when we are defining computed
2255  // fields in a Proxy. In these cases use the slow stub to invoke the
2256  // define trap.
2257  if (IsDefineNamedOwnIC() || IsDefineKeyedOwnIC()) {
2258  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreIC_SlowStub);
2259  return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate()));
2260  }
2261 
2262  return MaybeObjectHandle(StoreHandler::StoreProxy(
2263  isolate(), lookup_start_object_map(), holder, receiver));
2264  }
2265 
2266  case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
2267  case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
2268  case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
2269  case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
2270  case LookupIterator::STRING_LOOKUP_START_OBJECT:
2271  UNREACHABLE();
2272  }
2273  return MaybeObjectHandle();
2274 }

2276 void KeyedStoreIC::UpdateStoreElement(Handle<Map> receiver_map,
2277  KeyedAccessStoreMode store_mode,
2278  Handle<Map> new_receiver_map) {
2279  MapsAndHandlers target_maps_and_handlers(isolate());
2280  nexus()->ExtractMapsAndHandlers(
2281  &target_maps_and_handlers,
2282  [this](Handle<Map> map) { return Map::TryUpdate(isolate(), map); });
2283  if (target_maps_and_handlers.empty()) {
2284  DirectHandle<Map> monomorphic_map = receiver_map;
2285  // If we transitioned to a map that is a more general map than incoming
2286  // then use the new map.
2287  if (IsTransitionOfMonomorphicTarget(*receiver_map, *new_receiver_map)) {
2288  monomorphic_map = new_receiver_map;
2289  }
2290  DirectHandle<Object> handler =
2291  StoreElementHandler(monomorphic_map, store_mode);
2292  return ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name>(), monomorphic_map, handler);
2293  }
2294 
2295  for (DirectHandle<Map> map : target_maps_and_handlers.maps()) {
2296  if (!map.is_null() && map->instance_type() == JS_PRIMITIVE_WRAPPER_TYPE) {
2297  DCHECK(!IsStoreInArrayLiteralIC());
2298  set_slow_stub_reason("JSPrimitiveWrapper");
2299  return;
2300  }
2301  }
2302 
2303  // There are several special cases where an IC that is MONOMORPHIC can still
2304  // transition to a different IC that handles a superset of the original IC.
2305  // Handle those here if the receiver map hasn't changed or it has transitioned
2306  // to a more general kind.
2307  KeyedAccessStoreMode old_store_mode = GetKeyedAccessStoreMode();
2308  DirectHandle<Map> previous_receiver_map = target_maps_and_handlers.maps()[0];
2309  if (state() == MONOMORPHIC) {
2310  DirectHandle<Map> transitioned_receiver_map = new_receiver_map;
2311  if (IsTransitionOfMonomorphicTarget(*previous_receiver_map,
2312  *transitioned_receiver_map)) {
2313  // If the "old" and "new" maps are in the same elements map family, or
2314  // if they at least come from the same origin for a transitioning store,
2315  // stay MONOMORPHIC and use the map for the most generic ElementsKind.
2316  DirectHandle<Object> handler =
2317  StoreElementHandler(transitioned_receiver_map, store_mode);
2318  ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name>(), transitioned_receiver_map,
2319  handler);
2320  return;
2321  }
2322  // If there is no transition and if we have seen the same map earlier and
2323  // there is only a change in the store_mode we can still stay monomorphic.
2324  if (receiver_map.is_identical_to(previous_receiver_map) &&
2325  new_receiver_map.is_identical_to(receiver_map) &&
2326  StoreModeIsInBounds(old_store_mode) &&
2327  !StoreModeIsInBounds(store_mode)) {
2328  if (IsJSArrayMap(*receiver_map) &&
2329  JSArray::MayHaveReadOnlyLength(*receiver_map)) {
2330  set_slow_stub_reason(
2331  "can't generalize store mode (potentially read-only length)");
2332  return;
2333  }
2334  // A "normal" IC that handles stores can switch to a version that can
2335  // grow at the end of the array, handle OOB accesses or copy COW arrays
2336  // and still stay MONOMORPHIC.
2337  DirectHandle<Object> handler =
2338  StoreElementHandler(receiver_map, store_mode);
2339  return ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name>(), receiver_map, handler);
2340  }
2341  }
2342 
2343  DCHECK(state() != GENERIC);
2344 
2345  bool map_added =
2346  AddOneReceiverMapIfMissing(&target_maps_and_handlers, receiver_map);
2347 
2348  if (IsTransitionOfMonomorphicTarget(*receiver_map, *new_receiver_map)) {
2349  map_added |=
2350  AddOneReceiverMapIfMissing(&target_maps_and_handlers, new_receiver_map);
2351  }
2352 
2353  if (!map_added) {
2354  // If the miss wasn't due to an unseen map, a polymorphic stub
2355  // won't help, use the megamorphic stub which can handle everything.
2356  set_slow_stub_reason("same map added twice");
2357  return;
2358  }
2359 
2360  // If the maximum number of receiver maps has been exceeded, use the
2361  // megamorphic version of the IC.
2362  if (static_cast<int>(target_maps_and_handlers.size()) >
2363  v8_flags.max_valid_polymorphic_map_count) {
2364  return;
2365  }
2366 
2367  // Make sure all polymorphic handlers have the same store mode, otherwise the
2368  // megamorphic stub must be used.
2369  if (!StoreModeIsInBounds(old_store_mode)) {
2370  if (StoreModeIsInBounds(store_mode)) {
2371  store_mode = old_store_mode;
2372  } else if (store_mode != old_store_mode) {
2373  set_slow_stub_reason("store mode mismatch");
2374  return;
2375  }
2376  }
2377 
2378  // If the store mode isn't the standard mode, make sure that all polymorphic
2379  // receivers are either external arrays, or all "normal" arrays with writable
2380  // length. Otherwise, use the megamorphic stub.
2381  if (!StoreModeIsInBounds(store_mode)) {
2382  size_t external_arrays = 0;
2383  for (DirectHandle<Map> map : target_maps_and_handlers.maps()) {
2384  if (IsJSArrayMap(*map) && JSArray::MayHaveReadOnlyLength(*map)) {
2385  set_slow_stub_reason(
2386  "unsupported combination of arrays (potentially read-only length)");
2387  return;
2388 
2389  } else if (map->has_typed_array_or_rab_gsab_typed_array_elements()) {
2390  DCHECK(!IsStoreInArrayLiteralIC());
2391  external_arrays++;
2392  }
2393  }
2394  if (external_arrays != 0 &&
2395  external_arrays != target_maps_and_handlers.size()) {
2396  DCHECK(!IsStoreInArrayLiteralIC());
2397  set_slow_stub_reason(
2398  "unsupported combination of external and normal arrays");
2399  return;
2400  }
2401  }
2402 
2403  StoreElementPolymorphicHandlers(&target_maps_and_handlers, store_mode);
2404  if (target_maps_and_handlers.empty()) {
2405  DirectHandle<Object> handler =
2406  StoreElementHandler(receiver_map, store_mode);
2407  ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name>(), receiver_map, handler);
2408  } else if (target_maps_and_handlers.size() == 1) {
2409  auto [map, handler] = target_maps_and_handlers[0];
2410  ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name>(), map, handler);
2411  } else {
2412  ConfigureVectorState(DirectHandle<Name>(), target_maps_and_handlers);
2413  }
2414 }
2415 
2416 Handle<Object> KeyedStoreIC::StoreElementHandler(
2417  DirectHandle<Map> receiver_map, KeyedAccessStoreMode store_mode,
2418  MaybeDirectHandle<UnionOf<Smi, Cell>> prev_validity_cell) {
2419  if (!IsJSObjectMap(*receiver_map)) {
2420  // DefineKeyedOwnIC, which is used to define computed fields in instances,
2421  // should handled by the slow stub below instead of the proxy stub.
2422  if (IsJSProxyMap(*receiver_map) && !IsDefineKeyedOwnIC()) {
2423  return StoreHandler::StoreProxy(isolate());
2424  }
2425 
2426 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2427  if (IsWasmObjectMap(*receiver_map)) {
2428  set_slow_stub_reason("wasm object");
2429  }
2430 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2431 
2432  // Wasm objects or other kind of special objects go through the slow stub.
2433  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), KeyedStoreIC_SlowStub);
2434  return StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate(), store_mode);
2435  }
2436 
2437  // The only case when could keep using non-slow element store handler for
2438  // a fast array with potentially read-only elements is when it's an
2439  // initializing store to array literal.
2440  DCHECK_IMPLIES(
2441  !receiver_map->has_dictionary_elements() &&
2442  receiver_map->ShouldCheckForReadOnlyElementsInPrototypeChain(
2443  isolate()),
2444  IsStoreInArrayLiteralIC());
2445 
2446  // TODO(ishell): move to StoreHandler::StoreElement().
2447  Handle<Code> code;
2448  if (receiver_map->has_sloppy_arguments_elements()) {
2449  // TODO(jgruber): Update counter name.
2450  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), KeyedStoreIC_KeyedStoreSloppyArgumentsStub);
2451  code = StoreHandler::StoreSloppyArgumentsBuiltin(isolate(), store_mode);
2452  } else if (receiver_map->has_fast_elements() ||
2453  receiver_map->has_sealed_elements() ||
2454  receiver_map->has_nonextensible_elements() ||
2455  receiver_map->has_typed_array_or_rab_gsab_typed_array_elements()) {
2456  // TODO(jgruber): Update counter name.
2457  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), KeyedStoreIC_StoreFastElementStub);
2458  if (IsJSArgumentsObjectMap(*receiver_map) &&
2459  receiver_map->has_fast_packed_elements()) {
2460  // Allow fast behaviour for in-bounds stores while making it miss and
2461  // properly handle the out of bounds store case.
2462  code = StoreHandler::StoreFastElementBuiltin(
2463  isolate(), KeyedAccessStoreMode::kInBounds);
2464  } else {
2465  code = StoreHandler::StoreFastElementBuiltin(isolate(), store_mode);
2466  if (receiver_map->has_typed_array_or_rab_gsab_typed_array_elements()) {
2467  return code;
2468  }
2469  }
2470  } else if (IsStoreInArrayLiteralIC()) {
2471  // TODO(jgruber): Update counter name.
2472  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), StoreInArrayLiteralIC_SlowStub);
2473  return StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate(), store_mode);
2474  } else {
2475  // TODO(jgruber): Update counter name.
2476  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), KeyedStoreIC_StoreElementStub);
2477  DCHECK(DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS == receiver_map->elements_kind() ||
2478  receiver_map->has_frozen_elements());
2479  return StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate(), store_mode);
2480  }
2481 
2482  if (IsAnyDefineOwn() || IsStoreInArrayLiteralIC()) return code;
2483  DirectHandle<UnionOf<Smi, Cell>> validity_cell;
2484  if (!prev_validity_cell.ToHandle(&validity_cell)) {
2485  validity_cell =
2486  Map::GetOrCreatePrototypeChainValidityCell(receiver_map, isolate());
2487  }
2488  if (IsSmi(*validity_cell)) {
2489  // There's no prototype validity cell to check, so we can just use the stub.
2490  return code;
2491  }
2492  Handle<StoreHandler> handler = isolate()->factory()->NewStoreHandler(0);
2493  handler->set_validity_cell(*validity_cell);
2494  handler->set_smi_handler(*code);
2495  return handler;
2496 }

2498 void KeyedStoreIC::StoreElementPolymorphicHandlers(
2499  MapsAndHandlers* receiver_maps_and_handlers,
2500  KeyedAccessStoreMode store_mode) {
2501  DirectHandleVector<Map> receiver_maps(isolate());
2502  receiver_maps.reserve(receiver_maps_and_handlers->size());
2503  for (DirectHandle<Map> map : receiver_maps_and_handlers->maps()) {
2504  receiver_maps.push_back(map);
2505  }
2506  for (size_t i = 0; i < receiver_maps_and_handlers->size(); i++) {
2507  auto [receiver_map, old_handler] = (*receiver_maps_and_handlers)[i];
2508  DCHECK(!receiver_map->is_deprecated());
2509  DirectHandle<Object> handler;
2510  DirectHandle<Map> transition;
2511 
2512  if (receiver_map->instance_type() < FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE ||
2513  receiver_map->ShouldCheckForReadOnlyElementsInPrototypeChain(
2514  isolate())) {
2515  // TODO(mvstanton): Consider embedding store_mode in the state of the slow
2516  // keyed store ic for uniformity.
2517  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(), KeyedStoreIC_SlowStub);
2518  handler = StoreHandler::StoreSlow(isolate());
2519 
2520  } else {
2521  {
2522  Tagged<Map> tmap = receiver_map->FindElementsKindTransitionedMap(
2523  isolate(),
2524  MapHandlesSpan(receiver_maps.begin(), receiver_maps.end()),
2525  ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous);
2526  if (!tmap.is_null()) {
2527  if (receiver_map->is_stable()) {
2528  receiver_map->NotifyLeafMapLayoutChange(isolate());
2529  }
2530  transition = direct_handle(tmap, isolate());
2531  }
2532  }
2533 
2534  MaybeDirectHandle<UnionOf<Smi, Cell>> validity_cell;
2535  Tagged<HeapObject> old_handler_obj;
2536  if (!old_handler.is_null() &&
2537  (*old_handler).GetHeapObject(&old_handler_obj) &&
2538  IsDataHandler(old_handler_obj)) {
2539  validity_cell = direct_handle(
2540  Cast<DataHandler>(old_handler_obj)->validity_cell(), isolate());
2541  }
2542  // TODO(mythria): Do not recompute the handler if we know there is no
2543  // change in the handler.
2544  // TODO(mvstanton): The code below is doing pessimistic elements
2545  // transitions. I would like to stop doing that and rely on Allocation
2546  // Site Tracking to do a better job of ensuring the data types are what
2547  // they need to be. Not all the elements are in place yet, pessimistic
2548  // elements transitions are still important for performance.
2549  if (!transition.is_null()) {
2550  TRACE_HANDLER_STATS(isolate(),
2551  KeyedStoreIC_ElementsTransitionAndStoreStub);
2552  handler = StoreHandler::StoreElementTransition(
2553  isolate(), receiver_map, transition, store_mode, validity_cell);
2554  } else {
2555  handler = StoreElementHandler(receiver_map, store_mode, validity_cell);
2556  }
2557  }
2558  DCHECK(!handler.is_null());
2559  receiver_maps_and_handlers->set_map(i, receiver_map);
2560  receiver_maps_and_handlers->set_handler(i,
2561  MaybeObjectDirectHandle(handler));
2562  }
2563 }

2567 bool MayHaveTypedArrayInPrototypeChain(Isolate* isolate,
2568  DirectHandle<JSObject> object) {
2569  for (PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, *object); !iter.IsAtEnd();
2570  iter.Advance()) {
2571  // Be conservative, don't walk into proxies.
2572  if (IsJSProxy(iter.GetCurrent())) return true;
2573  if (IsJSTypedArray(iter.GetCurrent())) return true;
2574  }
2575  return false;
2576 }
2577 
2578 KeyedAccessStoreMode GetStoreMode(DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver,
2579  size_t index) {
2580  bool oob_access = IsOutOfBoundsAccess(receiver, index);
2581  // Don't consider this a growing store if the store would send the receiver to
2582  // dictionary mode.
2583  bool allow_growth =
2584  IsJSArray(*receiver) && oob_access && index <= JSArray::kMaxArrayIndex &&
2585  !receiver->WouldConvertToSlowElements(static_cast<uint32_t>(index));
2586  if (allow_growth) {
2587  return KeyedAccessStoreMode::kGrowAndHandleCOW;
2588  }
2589  if (receiver->map()->has_typed_array_or_rab_gsab_typed_array_elements() &&
2590  oob_access) {
2591  return KeyedAccessStoreMode::kIgnoreTypedArrayOOB;
2592  }
2593  return receiver->elements()->IsCowArray() ? KeyedAccessStoreMode::kHandleCOW
2594  : KeyedAccessStoreMode::kInBounds;
2595 }

2599 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> KeyedStoreIC::Store(Handle<JSAny> object,
2600  Handle<Object> key,
2601  DirectHandle<Object> value) {
2602  // TODO(verwaest): Let SetProperty do the migration, since storing a property
2603  // might deprecate the current map again, if value does not fit.
2604  if (MigrateDeprecated(isolate(), object)) {
2605  DirectHandle<Object> result;
2606  // TODO(v8:12548): refactor DefineKeyedOwnIC as a subclass of StoreIC
2607  // so the logic doesn't get mixed here.
2608  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2609  isolate(), result,
2610  IsDefineKeyedOwnIC()
2611  ? Runtime::DefineObjectOwnProperty(isolate(), object, key, value,
2612  StoreOrigin::kNamed)
2613  : Runtime::SetObjectProperty(isolate(), object, key, value,
2614  StoreOrigin::kMaybeKeyed));
2615  return result;
2616  }
2617 
2618  DirectHandle<Object> store_handle;
2619 
2620  intptr_t maybe_index;
2621  Handle<Name> maybe_name;
2622  KeyType key_type = TryConvertKey(key, isolate(), &maybe_index, &maybe_name);
2623 
2624  if (key_type == kName) {
2625  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2626  isolate(), store_handle,
2627  StoreIC::Store(object, maybe_name, value, StoreOrigin::kMaybeKeyed));
2628  if (vector_needs_update()) {
2629  if (ConfigureVectorState(MEGAMORPHIC, key)) {
2630  set_slow_stub_reason("unhandled internalized string key");
2631  TraceIC("StoreIC", key);
2632  }
2633  }
2634  return store_handle;
2635  }
2636 
2637  JSObject::MakePrototypesFast(object, kStartAtPrototype, isolate());
2638 
2639  // TODO(jkummerow): Refactor the condition logic here and below.
2640  bool use_ic = (state() != NO_FEEDBACK) && v8_flags.use_ic &&
2641  !IsStringWrapper(*object) && !IsAccessCheckNeeded(*object) &&
2642  !IsJSGlobalProxy(*object);
2643  if (use_ic && !IsSmi(*object)) {
2644  // Don't use ICs for maps of the objects in Array's prototype chain. We
2645  // expect to be able to trap element sets to objects with those maps in
2646  // the runtime to enable optimization of element hole access.
2647  DirectHandle<HeapObject> heap_object = Cast<HeapObject>(object);
2648  if (heap_object->map()->IsMapInArrayPrototypeChain(isolate())) {
2649  set_slow_stub_reason("map in array prototype");
2650  use_ic = false;
2651  }
2652  }
2653 
2654  Handle<Map> old_receiver_map;
2655  bool is_arguments = false;
2656  bool key_is_valid_index = (key_type == kIntPtr);
2657  KeyedAccessStoreMode store_mode = KeyedAccessStoreMode::kInBounds;
2658  if (use_ic && IsJSReceiver(*object) && key_is_valid_index) {
2659  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver = Cast<JSReceiver>(object);
2660  old_receiver_map = handle(receiver->map(), isolate());
2661  is_arguments = IsJSArgumentsObject(*receiver);
2662  bool is_jsobject = IsJSObject(*receiver);
2663  size_t index;
2664  key_is_valid_index = IntPtrKeyToSize(maybe_index, receiver, &index);
2665  if (is_jsobject && !is_arguments && key_is_valid_index) {
2666  DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver_object = Cast<JSObject>(object);
2667  store_mode = GetStoreMode(receiver_object, index);
2668  }
2669  }
2670 
2671  DCHECK(store_handle.is_null());
2672  // TODO(v8:12548): refactor DefineKeyedOwnIC as a subclass of StoreIC
2673  // so the logic doesn't get mixed here.
2674  MaybeDirectHandle<Object> result =
2675  IsDefineKeyedOwnIC()
2676  ? Runtime::DefineObjectOwnProperty(isolate(), object, key, value,
2677  StoreOrigin::kNamed)
2678  : Runtime::SetObjectProperty(isolate(), object, key, value,
2679  StoreOrigin::kMaybeKeyed);
2680  if (result.is_null()) {
2681  DCHECK(isolate()->has_exception());
2682  set_slow_stub_reason("failed to set property");
2683  use_ic = false;
2684  }
2685  if (use_ic) {
2686  if (!old_receiver_map.is_null()) {
2687  if (is_arguments) {
2688  set_slow_stub_reason("arguments receiver");
2689  } else if (IsJSArray(*object) && StoreModeCanGrow(store_mode) &&
2690  JSArray::HasReadOnlyLength(Cast<JSArray>(object))) {
2691  set_slow_stub_reason("array has read only length");
2692  } else if (IsJSObject(*object) &&
2693  MayHaveTypedArrayInPrototypeChain(isolate(),
2694  Cast<JSObject>(object))) {
2695  // Make sure we don't handle this in IC if there's any JSTypedArray in
2696  // the {receiver}'s prototype chain, since that prototype is going to
2697  // swallow all stores that are out-of-bounds for said prototype, and we
2698  // just let the runtime deal with the complexity of this.
2699  set_slow_stub_reason("typed array in the prototype chain");
2700  } else if (key_is_valid_index) {
2701  if (old_receiver_map->is_abandoned_prototype_map()) {
2702  set_slow_stub_reason("receiver with prototype map");
2703 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2704  } else if (IsWasmObjectMap(*old_receiver_map)) {
2705  // Handle object types for which we don't need to check for
2706  // read-only prototype elements because we'll use the slow handler
2707  // anyway.
2708  DirectHandle<HeapObject> receiver = Cast<HeapObject>(object);
2709  UpdateStoreElement(old_receiver_map, store_mode,
2710  handle(receiver->map(), isolate()));
2711 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2712  } else if (old_receiver_map->has_dictionary_elements() ||
2713  !old_receiver_map
2714  ->ShouldCheckForReadOnlyElementsInPrototypeChain(
2715  isolate())) {
2716  // We should go generic if receiver isn't a dictionary, but our
2717  // prototype chain does have dictionary elements. This ensures that
2718  // other non-dictionary receivers in the polymorphic case benefit
2719  // from fast path keyed stores.
2720  DirectHandle<HeapObject> receiver = Cast<HeapObject>(object);
2721  UpdateStoreElement(old_receiver_map, store_mode,
2722  handle(receiver->map(), isolate()));
2723  } else {
2724  set_slow_stub_reason("prototype with potentially read-only elements");
2725  }
2726  } else {
2727  set_slow_stub_reason("non-smi-like key");
2728  }
2729  } else {
2730  set_slow_stub_reason("non-JSObject receiver");
2731  }
2732  }
2733 
2734  if (vector_needs_update()) {
2735  ConfigureVectorState(MEGAMORPHIC, key);
2736  }
2737  TraceIC("StoreIC", key);
2738 
2739  return result;
2740 }

2800 RUNTIME_FUNCTION(Runtime_LoadIC_Miss) {
2801  HandleScope scope(isolate);
2802  DCHECK_EQ(4, args.length());
2803  // Runtime functions don't follow the IC's calling convention.
2804  Handle<JSAny> receiver = args.at<JSAny>(0);
2805  Handle<Name> key = args.at<Name>(1);
2806  int slot = args.tagged_index_value_at(2);
2807  Handle<FeedbackVector> vector = args.at<FeedbackVector>(3);
2808  FeedbackSlot vector_slot = FeedbackVector::ToSlot(slot);
2809 
2810  // A monomorphic or polymorphic KeyedLoadIC with a string key can call the
2811  // LoadIC miss handler if the handler misses. Since the vector Nexus is
2812  // set up outside the IC, handle that here.
2813  FeedbackSlotKind kind = vector->GetKind(vector_slot);
2814  if (IsLoadICKind(kind)) {
2815  LoadIC ic(isolate, vector, vector_slot, kind);
2816  ic.UpdateState(receiver, key);
2817  RETURN_RESULT_OR_FAILURE(isolate, ic.Load(receiver, key));
2818 
2819  } else if (IsLoadGlobalICKind(kind)) {
2820  DCHECK_EQ(isolate->native_context()->global_proxy(), *receiver);
2821  receiver = isolate->global_object();
2822  LoadGlobalIC ic(isolate, vector, vector_slot, kind);
2823  ic.UpdateState(receiver, key);
2824  RETURN_RESULT_OR_FAILURE(isolate, ic.Load(key));

3280 enum class FastCloneObjectMode {
3281  // The clone has the same map as the input.
3282  kIdenticalMap,
3283  // The clone is the empty object literal.
3284  kEmptyObject,
3285  // The clone has an empty object literal map.
3286  kDifferentMap,
3287  // The source map is to complicated to handle.
3288  kNotSupported,
3289  // Returned by PreCheck
3290  kMaybeSupported
3291 };
3292 
3293 FastCloneObjectMode GetCloneModeForMapPreCheck(DirectHandle<Map> map,
3294  bool null_proto_literal,
3295  Isolate* isolate) {
3296  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3297  if (!IsJSObjectMap(*map)) {
3298  // Everything that produces the empty object literal can be supported since
3299  // we have a special case for that.
3300  if (null_proto_literal) return FastCloneObjectMode::kNotSupported;
3301  return IsNullOrUndefinedMap(*map) || IsBooleanMap(*map) ||
3302  IsHeapNumberMap(*map)
3303  ? FastCloneObjectMode::kEmptyObject
3304  : FastCloneObjectMode::kNotSupported;
3305  }
3306  ElementsKind elements_kind = map->elements_kind();
3307  if (!IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(elements_kind) &&
3308  !IsAnyNonextensibleElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
3309  return FastCloneObjectMode::kNotSupported;
3310  }
3311  if (!map->OnlyHasSimpleProperties()) {
3312  return FastCloneObjectMode::kNotSupported;
3313  }
3314 
3315  // TODO(olivf): Think about cases where cross-context copies are safe.
3316  if (!map->BelongsToSameNativeContextAs(isolate->context())) {
3317  return FastCloneObjectMode::kNotSupported;
3318  }
3319 
3320  return FastCloneObjectMode::kMaybeSupported;
3321 }
3322 
3323 FastCloneObjectMode GetCloneModeForMap(DirectHandle<Map> map,
3324  bool null_proto_literal,
3325  Isolate* isolate) {
3326  FastCloneObjectMode pre_check =
3327  GetCloneModeForMapPreCheck(map, null_proto_literal, isolate);
3328  if (pre_check != FastCloneObjectMode::kMaybeSupported) {
3329  return pre_check;
3330  }
3331 
3332  // The clone must always start from an object literal map, it must be an
3333  // instance of the object function, have the default prototype and not be a
3334  // prototype itself. Only if the source map fits that criterion we can
3335  // directly use it as the target map.
3336  FastCloneObjectMode mode =
3337  map->instance_type() == JS_OBJECT_TYPE &&
3338  !IsAnyNonextensibleElementsKind(map->elements_kind()) &&
3339  map->GetConstructor() == *isolate->object_function() &&
3340  map->prototype() == *isolate->object_function_prototype() &&
3341  !map->is_prototype_map()
3342  ? FastCloneObjectMode::kIdenticalMap
3343  : FastCloneObjectMode::kDifferentMap;
3344 
3345  if (null_proto_literal || IsNull(map->prototype())) {
3346  mode = FastCloneObjectMode::kDifferentMap;
3347  }
3348 
3349  Tagged<DescriptorArray> descriptors = map->instance_descriptors();
3350  for (InternalIndex i : map->IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
3351  PropertyDetails details = descriptors->GetDetails(i);
3352  Tagged<Name> key = descriptors->GetKey(i);
3353  if (details.kind() != PropertyKind::kData || !details.IsEnumerable() ||
3354  key->IsPrivateName()) {
3355  return FastCloneObjectMode::kNotSupported;
3356  }
3357  if (!details.IsConfigurable() || details.IsReadOnly()) {
3358  mode = FastCloneObjectMode::kDifferentMap;
3359  }
3360  }
3361 
3362  DCHECK_IMPLIES(mode == FastCloneObjectMode::kIdenticalMap,
3363  !map->is_prototype_map());
3364 
3365  return mode;
3366 }
3367 
3368 bool CanCacheCloneTargetMapTransition(
3369  DirectHandle<Map> source_map, std::optional<DirectHandle<Map>> target_map,
3370  bool null_proto_literal, Isolate* isolate) {
3371  if (!v8_flags.clone_object_sidestep_transitions || null_proto_literal) {
3372  return false;
3373  }
3374  // As of now any R/O source object should end up in the kEmptyObject case, but
3375  // there is not really a way of ensuring it. Thus, we also check it below.
3376  // This is a performance dcheck. If it fails, the clone IC does not handle a
3377  // case it probably could.
3378  // TODO(olivf): Either remove that dcheck or move it to GetCloneModeForMap.
3379  DCHECK(!HeapLayout::InReadOnlySpace(*source_map));
3380  if (HeapLayout::InReadOnlySpace(*source_map) || source_map->is_deprecated() ||
3381  source_map->is_prototype_map()) {
3382  return false;
3383  }
3384  if (!target_map) {
3385  return true;
3386  }
3387  CHECK(!HeapLayout::InReadOnlySpace(**target_map));
3388  return !(*target_map)->is_deprecated();
3389 }
3390 
3391 // Check if an object with `source_map` can be cloned by `FastCloneJSObject`
3392 // when the result shall have `target_map`. Optionally `override_map` is the map
3393 // of an already existing object that will be written into. If no `override_map`
3394 // is given, we assume that a fresh target object can be allocated with
3395 // already the correct `target_map`.
3396 bool CanFastCloneObjectToObjectLiteral(DirectHandle<Map> source_map,
3397  DirectHandle<Map> target_map,
3398  DirectHandle<Map> override_map,
3399  bool null_proto_literal,
3400  Isolate* isolate) {
3401  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3402  DCHECK(!target_map->is_deprecated());
3403  DCHECK(source_map->OnlyHasSimpleProperties());
3404  DCHECK(!source_map->IsInobjectSlackTrackingInProgress());
3405  DCHECK(!target_map->IsInobjectSlackTrackingInProgress());
3406  DCHECK_EQ(*target_map->map(), *source_map->map());
3407  DCHECK_EQ(target_map->GetConstructor(), *isolate->object_function());
3408  DCHECK_IMPLIES(
3409  !null_proto_literal,
3410  *target_map->prototype() == *isolate->object_function_prototype());
3411 
3412  // Ensure source and target have identical binary representation of properties
3413  // and elements as the IC relies on copying the raw bytes. This also excludes
3414  // cases with non-enumerable properties or accessors on the source object.
3415  if (source_map->instance_type() != JS_OBJECT_TYPE ||
3416  target_map->instance_type() != JS_OBJECT_TYPE ||
3417  !target_map->OnlyHasSimpleProperties() ||
3418  !target_map->has_fast_elements()) {
3419  return false;
3420  }
3421  if (!override_map.is_null()) {
3422  // No cross-context object reuse.
3423  if (target_map->map() != override_map->map()) {
3424  return false;
3425  }
3426  // In case we want to clone into an existing target object, we must ensure
3427  // that this existing object has a compatible size. In particular we cannot
3428  // shrink or grow the already given object. We also exclude a different
3429  // start offset, since this doesn't allow us to change the object in-place
3430  // in a GC safe way.
3431  DCHECK_EQ(*override_map, isolate->object_function()->initial_map());
3432  DCHECK(override_map->instance_type() == JS_OBJECT_TYPE);
3433  DCHECK_EQ(override_map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors(), 0);
3434  DCHECK(!override_map->IsInobjectSlackTrackingInProgress());
3435  if (override_map->instance_size() != target_map->instance_size() ||
3436  override_map->GetInObjectPropertiesStartInWords() !=
3437  target_map->GetInObjectPropertiesStartInWords()) {
3438  return false;
3439  }
3440  }
3441 #ifdef DEBUG
3442  ElementsKind source_elements_kind = source_map->elements_kind();
3443  ElementsKind target_elements_kind = target_map->elements_kind();
3444  DCHECK(IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(source_elements_kind) ||
3445  IsAnyNonextensibleElementsKind(source_elements_kind));
3446  DCHECK(IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(target_elements_kind));
3447  DCHECK_IMPLIES(IsHoleyElementsKindForRead(source_elements_kind),
3448  IsHoleyElementsKind(target_elements_kind));
3449 #endif // DEBUG
3450  // There are no transitions between prototype maps.
3451  if (source_map->is_prototype_map() || target_map->is_prototype_map()) {
3452  return false;
3453  }
3454  // Exclude edge-cases like not copying a __proto__ property.
3455  if (source_map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors() !=
3456  target_map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors()) {
3457  return false;
3458  }
3459  // Check that the source inobject properties fit into the target.
3460  int source_used_inobj_properties = source_map->GetInObjectProperties() -
3461  source_map->UnusedInObjectProperties();
3462  int target_used_inobj_properties = target_map->GetInObjectProperties() -
3463  target_map->UnusedInObjectProperties();
3464  if (source_used_inobj_properties != target_used_inobj_properties) {
3465  return false;
3466  }
3467  // The properties backing store must be of the same size as the clone ic again
3468  // blindly copies it.
3469  if (source_map->HasOutOfObjectProperties() !=
3470  target_map->HasOutOfObjectProperties() ||
3471  (target_map->HasOutOfObjectProperties() &&
3472  source_map->UnusedPropertyFields() !=
3473  target_map->UnusedPropertyFields())) {
3474  return false;
3475  }
3476  Tagged<DescriptorArray> descriptors = source_map->instance_descriptors();
3477  Tagged<DescriptorArray> target_descriptors =
3478  target_map->instance_descriptors();
3479  for (InternalIndex i : target_map->IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
3480  if (descriptors->GetKey(i) != target_descriptors->GetKey(i)) {
3481  return false;
3482  }
3483  PropertyDetails details = descriptors->GetDetails(i);
3484  PropertyDetails target_details = target_descriptors->GetDetails(i);
3485  DCHECK_EQ(details.kind(), PropertyKind::kData);
3486  DCHECK_EQ(target_details.kind(), PropertyKind::kData);
3487  Tagged<FieldType> type = descriptors->GetFieldType(i);
3488  Tagged<FieldType> target_type = target_descriptors->GetFieldType(i);
3489  // This DCHECK rests on the fact that we only clear field types when there
3490  // are no instances of the host map left. Thus, to enter the clone IC at
3491  // least one object of the source map needs to be created, which in turn
3492  // will re-initialize the source maps field type. This is guaranteed to also
3493  // update the target map through the sidestep transition, unless the target
3494  // map is deprecated.
3495  DCHECK(!IsNone(type));
3496  DCHECK(!IsNone(target_type));
3497  // With move_prototype_transitions_first enabled field updates don't
3498  // generalize across prototype transitions, because the transitions happen
3499  // on root maps (i.e., before any field is added). In other words we cannot
3500  // rely on changes in the source map propagating to the target map when
3501  // there is a SetPrototype involved. NB, technically without
3502  // move_prototype_transitions_first we also don't update field types across
3503  // prototype transitions, however we preemptively generalize all fields of
3504  // prototype transition target maps.
3505  bool prototype_transition_is_shortcutted =
3506  v8_flags.move_prototype_transitions_first &&
3507  source_map->prototype() != target_map->prototype();
3508  if (!prototype_transition_is_shortcutted &&
3509  CanCacheCloneTargetMapTransition(source_map, target_map,
3510  null_proto_literal, isolate)) {
3511  if (!details.representation().fits_into(
3512  target_details.representation()) ||
3513  (target_details.representation().IsDouble() &&
3514  details.representation().IsSmi())) {
3515  return false;
3516  }
3517  if (!FieldType::NowIs(type, target_type)) {
3518  return false;
3519  }
3520  } else {
3521  // In the case we cannot connect the maps in the transition tree (e.g.,
3522  // the clone also involves a proto transition) we cannot keep track of
3523  // representation dependencies. We can only allow the most generic target
3524  // representation. The same goes for field types.
3525  if (!details.representation().MostGenericInPlaceChange().Equals(
3526  target_details.representation()) ||
3527  !IsAny(target_type)) {
3528  return false;
3529  }
3530  }
3531  }
3532  return true;
3533 }

3537 static MaybeDirectHandle<JSObject> CloneObjectSlowPath(
3538  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> source, int flags) {
3539  DirectHandle<JSObject> new_object;
3540  if (flags & ObjectLiteral::kHasNullPrototype) {
3541  new_object = isolate->factory()->NewJSObjectWithNullProto();
3542  } else if (IsJSObject(*source) &&
3543  Cast<JSObject>(*source)->map()->OnlyHasSimpleProperties()) {
3544  Tagged<Map> source_map = Cast<JSObject>(*source)->map();
3545  // TODO(olivf, chrome:1204540) It might be interesting to pick a map with
3546  // more properties, depending how many properties are added by the
3547  // surrounding literal.
3548  int properties = source_map->GetInObjectProperties() -
3549  source_map->UnusedInObjectProperties();
3550  DirectHandle<Map> map = isolate->factory()->ObjectLiteralMapFromCache(
3551  isolate->native_context(), properties);
3552  new_object = isolate->factory()->NewFastOrSlowJSObjectFromMap(map);
3553  } else {
3554  DirectHandle<JSFunction> constructor(
3555  isolate->native_context()->object_function(), isolate);
3556  new_object = isolate->factory()->NewJSObject(constructor);
3557  }
3558 
3559  if (IsNullOrUndefined(*source)) {
3560  return new_object;
3561  }
3562 
3563  MAYBE_RETURN(
3564  JSReceiver::SetOrCopyDataProperties(
3565  isolate, new_object, source,
3566  PropertiesEnumerationMode::kPropertyAdditionOrder, {}, false),
3567  MaybeDirectHandle<JSObject>());
3568  return new_object;
3569 }

3574  DirectHandle<Object> source = args.at(0);
3575  int flags = args.smi_value_at(1);
3576  RETURN_RESULT_OR_FAILURE(isolate,
3577  CloneObjectSlowPath(isolate, source, flags));

3582 template <SideStepTransition::Kind kind>
3583 Tagged<Object> GetCloneTargetMap(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Map> source_map,
3584  DirectHandle<Map> override_map) {
3585  static_assert(kind == SideStepTransition::Kind::kObjectAssign ||
3586  kind == SideStepTransition::Kind::kCloneObject);
3587  if (!v8_flags.clone_object_sidestep_transitions) {
3588  return SideStepTransition::Empty;
3589  }
3590 
3591  // Ensure we can follow the sidestep transition NativeContext-wise.
3592  if (!source_map->BelongsToSameNativeContextAs(isolate->context())) {
3593  return SideStepTransition::Empty;
3594  }
3595  Tagged<Object> result = SideStepTransition::Empty;
3596  TransitionsAccessor transitions(isolate, *source_map);
3597  if (transitions.HasSideStepTransitions()) {
3598  result = transitions.GetSideStepTransition(kind);
3599  if (result.IsHeapObject()) {
3600  // Exclude deprecated maps.
3601  auto map = Cast<Map>(result.GetHeapObject());
3602  bool is_valid = !map->is_deprecated();
3603  // In the case of object assign we need to check the prototype validity
3604  // cell on the override map. If the override map changed we cannot assume
3605  // that it is correct to set all properties without any getter/setter in
3606  // the prototype chain interfering.
3607  if constexpr (kind == SideStepTransition::Kind::kObjectAssign) {
3608  if (is_valid) {
3609  DCHECK_EQ(*override_map, isolate->object_function()->initial_map());
3610  Tagged<Object> validity_cell = transitions.GetSideStepTransition(
3611  SideStepTransition::Kind::kObjectAssignValidityCell);
3612  is_valid = validity_cell.IsHeapObject() &&
3613  Cast<Cell>(validity_cell)->value().ToSmi().value() ==
3614  Map::kPrototypeChainValid;
3615  }
3616  }
3617  if (V8_LIKELY(is_valid)) {
3618  if (result.IsHeapObject()) {
3619  CHECK_EQ(GetCloneModeForMapPreCheck(source_map, false, isolate),
3620  FastCloneObjectMode::kMaybeSupported);
3621  }
3622  } else {
3623  result = SideStepTransition::Empty;
3624  }
3625  }
3626  }
3627 #ifdef DEBUG
3628  FastCloneObjectMode clone_mode =
3629  GetCloneModeForMap(source_map, false, isolate);
3630  if (result == SideStepTransition::Unreachable) {
3631  switch (clone_mode) {
3632  case FastCloneObjectMode::kNotSupported:
3633  case FastCloneObjectMode::kDifferentMap:
3634  break;
3635  case FastCloneObjectMode::kEmptyObject:
3636  case FastCloneObjectMode::kIdenticalMap:
3637  DCHECK_EQ(kind, SideStepTransition::Kind::kObjectAssign);
3638  break;
3639  case FastCloneObjectMode::kMaybeSupported:
3640  UNREACHABLE();
3641  }
3642  } else if (result != SideStepTransition::Empty) {
3643  Tagged<Map> target = Cast<Map>(result.GetHeapObject());
3644  switch (clone_mode) {
3645  case FastCloneObjectMode::kIdenticalMap:
3646  if (kind == SideStepTransition::Kind::kCloneObject) {
3647  DCHECK_EQ(*source_map, target);
3648  break;
3649  }
3650  DCHECK_EQ(kind, SideStepTransition::Kind::kObjectAssign);
3651  [[fallthrough]];
3652  case FastCloneObjectMode::kDifferentMap:
3653  DCHECK(CanFastCloneObjectToObjectLiteral(source_map,
3654  direct_handle(target, isolate),
3655  override_map, false, isolate));
3656  break;
3657  default:
3658  UNREACHABLE();
3659  }
3660  } else {
3661  DCHECK_EQ(result, SideStepTransition::Empty);
3662  }
3663 #endif // DEBUG
3664  return result;
3665 }
3666 
3667 template <SideStepTransition::Kind kind>
3668 void SetCloneTargetMap(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Map> source_map,
3669  DirectHandle<Map> new_target_map,
3670  DirectHandle<Map> override_map) {
3671  if (!v8_flags.clone_object_sidestep_transitions) return;
3672  DCHECK(CanCacheCloneTargetMapTransition(source_map, new_target_map, false,
3673  isolate));
3674  DCHECK_EQ(GetCloneTargetMap<kind>(isolate, source_map, override_map),
3675  SideStepTransition::Empty);
3676  DCHECK(!new_target_map->is_deprecated());
3677 
3678  // Adding this transition also ensures that when the source map field
3679  // generalizes, we also generalize the target map.
3680  DCHECK(IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(new_target_map->elements_kind()));
3681 
3682  constexpr bool need_validity_cell =
3683  kind == SideStepTransition::Kind::kObjectAssign;
3684  DirectHandle<Cell> validity_cell;
3685  if constexpr (need_validity_cell) {
3686  // Since we only clone into empty object literals we only need one validity
3687  // cell on that prototype chain.
3688  DCHECK_EQ(*override_map, isolate->object_function()->initial_map());
3689  validity_cell = Cast<Cell>(
3690  Map::GetOrCreatePrototypeChainValidityCell(override_map, isolate));
3691  }
3692  TransitionsAccessor::EnsureHasSideStepTransitions(isolate, source_map);
3693  TransitionsAccessor transitions(isolate, *source_map);
3694  transitions.SetSideStepTransition(kind, *new_target_map);
3695  if constexpr (need_validity_cell) {
3696  transitions.SetSideStepTransition(
3697  SideStepTransition::Kind::kObjectAssignValidityCell, *validity_cell);
3698  }
3699  DCHECK_EQ(GetCloneTargetMap<kind>(isolate, source_map, override_map),
3700  *new_target_map);
3701 }
3702 
3703 template <SideStepTransition::Kind kind>
3704 void SetCloneTargetMapUnsupported(Isolate* isolate,
3705  DirectHandle<Map> source_map,
3706  DirectHandle<Map> override_map) {
3707  if (!v8_flags.clone_object_sidestep_transitions) return;
3708  DCHECK_EQ(GetCloneTargetMap<kind>(isolate, source_map, override_map),
3709  SideStepTransition::Empty);
3710  DCHECK(CanCacheCloneTargetMapTransition(source_map, {}, false, isolate));
3711  // Adding this transition also ensures that when the source map field
3712  // generalizes, we also generalize the target map.
3713  TransitionsAccessor::EnsureHasSideStepTransitions(isolate, source_map);
3714  TransitionsAccessor(isolate, *source_map)
3715  .SetSideStepTransition(kind, SideStepTransition::Unreachable);
3716  DCHECK_EQ(GetCloneTargetMap<kind>(isolate, source_map, override_map),
3717  SideStepTransition::Unreachable);
3718 }

3722 RUNTIME_FUNCTION(Runtime_CloneObjectIC_Miss) {
3723  HandleScope scope(isolate);
3724  DCHECK_EQ(4, args.length());
3725  DirectHandle<Object> source = args.at(0);
3726  int flags = args.smi_value_at(1);
3727 
3728  if (!MigrateDeprecated(isolate, source)) {
3729  Handle<HeapObject> maybe_vector = args.at<HeapObject>(3);
3730  std::optional<FeedbackNexus> nexus;
3731  if (IsFeedbackVector(*maybe_vector)) {
3732  int index = args.tagged_index_value_at(2);
3733  FeedbackSlot slot = FeedbackVector::ToSlot(index);
3734  nexus.emplace(isolate, Cast<FeedbackVector>(maybe_vector), slot);
3735  }
3736  if (!IsSmi(*source) && (!nexus || !nexus->IsMegamorphic())) {
3737  bool null_proto_literal = flags & ObjectLiteral::kHasNullPrototype;
3738  Handle<Map> source_map(Cast<HeapObject>(source)->map(), isolate);
3739 
3740  // In case we are still slack tracking let's defer a decision. The fast
3741  // case does not support it.
3742  if (!source_map->IsInobjectSlackTrackingInProgress()) {
3743  auto UpdateNexus = [&](Handle<Object> target_map) {
3744  if (!nexus) return;
3745  nexus->ConfigureCloneObject(source_map,
3746  MaybeObjectHandle(target_map));
3747  };
3748  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
3749  bool unsupported = false;
3750  if (!null_proto_literal) {
3751  auto maybe_target =
3752  GetCloneTargetMap<SideStepTransition::Kind::kCloneObject>(
3753  isolate, source_map, {});
3754  if (maybe_target == SideStepTransition::Unreachable) {
3755  unsupported = true;
3756  } else if (maybe_target != SideStepTransition::Empty) {
3757  Handle<Map> target =
3758  handle(Cast<Map>(maybe_target.GetHeapObject()), isolate);
3759  UpdateNexus(target);
3760  return *target;
3761  }
3762  }
3763 
3764  FastCloneObjectMode clone_mode =
3765  unsupported
3766  ? FastCloneObjectMode::kNotSupported
3767  : GetCloneModeForMap(source_map, null_proto_literal, isolate);
3768  auto UpdateState = [&](Handle<Map> target_map) {
3769  UpdateNexus(target_map);
3770  if (CanCacheCloneTargetMapTransition(source_map, target_map,
3771  null_proto_literal, isolate)) {
3772  SetCloneTargetMap<SideStepTransition::Kind::kCloneObject>(
3773  isolate, source_map, target_map, {});
3774  }
3775  };
3776  switch (clone_mode) {
3777  case FastCloneObjectMode::kIdenticalMap: {
3778  UpdateState(source_map);
3779  // When returning a map the IC miss handler re-starts from the top.
3780  return *source_map;
3781  }
3782  case FastCloneObjectMode::kEmptyObject: {
3783  UpdateNexus(handle(Smi::zero(), isolate));
3784  RETURN_RESULT_OR_FAILURE(
3785  isolate, CloneObjectSlowPath(isolate, source, flags));
3786  }
3787  case FastCloneObjectMode::kDifferentMap: {
3788  DirectHandle<Object> res;
3789  ASSIGN_RETURN_FAILURE_ON_EXCEPTION(
3790  isolate, res, CloneObjectSlowPath(isolate, source, flags));
3791  Handle<Map> result_map(Cast<HeapObject>(res)->map(), isolate);
3792  if (result_map->IsInobjectSlackTrackingInProgress()) {
3793  return *res;
3794  }
3795  if (CanFastCloneObjectToObjectLiteral(
3796  source_map, result_map, {}, null_proto_literal, isolate)) {
3797  DCHECK(result_map->OnlyHasSimpleProperties());
3798  DCHECK_EQ(source_map->GetInObjectProperties() -
3799  source_map->UnusedInObjectProperties(),
3800  result_map->GetInObjectProperties() -
3801  result_map->UnusedInObjectProperties());
3802  UpdateState(result_map);
3803  } else {
3804  if (CanCacheCloneTargetMapTransition(
3805  source_map, {}, null_proto_literal, isolate)) {
3806  SetCloneTargetMapUnsupported<
3807  SideStepTransition::Kind::kCloneObject>(isolate, source_map,
3808  {});
3809  }
3810  if (nexus) {
3811  nexus->ConfigureMegamorphic();
3812  }
3813  }
3814  return *res;
3815  }
3816  case FastCloneObjectMode::kNotSupported: {
3817  break;
3818  }
3819  case FastCloneObjectMode::kMaybeSupported:
3820  UNREACHABLE();
3821  }
3822  DCHECK(clone_mode == FastCloneObjectMode::kNotSupported);
3823  if (nexus) {
3824  nexus->ConfigureMegamorphic();
3825  }
3826  }
3827  }
3828  }
3829 
3830  RETURN_RESULT_OR_FAILURE(isolate,
3831  CloneObjectSlowPath(isolate, source, flags));
3832 }

3859 bool MaybeCanCloneObjectForObjectAssign(DirectHandle<JSReceiver> source,
3860  DirectHandle<Map> source_map,
3861  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target,
3862  Isolate* isolate) {
3863  FastCloneObjectMode clone_mode =
3864  GetCloneModeForMap(source_map, false, isolate);
3865  switch (clone_mode) {
3866  case FastCloneObjectMode::kIdenticalMap:
3867  case FastCloneObjectMode::kDifferentMap:
3868  break;
3869  case FastCloneObjectMode::kNotSupported:
3870  return false;
3871  case FastCloneObjectMode::kEmptyObject:
3872  case FastCloneObjectMode::kMaybeSupported:
3873  // Cannot happen since we should only be called with JSObjects.
3874  UNREACHABLE();
3875  }
3876 
3877  // We need to be sure that there are no setters or other nastiness installed
3878  // on the Object.prototype which clash with the properties we intende to copy.
3879  DirectHandle<FixedArray> keys;
3880  auto res =
3881  KeyAccumulator::GetKeys(isolate, source, KeyCollectionMode::kOwnOnly,
3882  ONLY_ENUMERABLE, GetKeysConversion::kKeepNumbers);
3883  CHECK(res.ToHandle(&keys));
3884  for (int i = 0; i < keys->length(); ++i) {
3885  Handle<Object> next_key(keys->get(i), isolate);
3886  PropertyKey key(isolate, next_key);
3887  LookupIterator it(isolate, target, key);
3888  switch (it.state()) {
3889  case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
3890  continue;
3891  case LookupIterator::DATA:
3892  if (it.property_attributes() & PropertyAttributes::READ_ONLY) {
3893  return false;
3894  }
3895  continue;
3896 
3897  case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR:
3898  case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
3899  case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
3900  case LookupIterator::JSPROXY:

3915 // Returns one of:
3916 // * A map to be used with FastCloneJSObject
3917 // * Undefined if fast cloning is not possible
3918 // * True if assignment must be skipped (i.e., the runtime already did it)
3919 RUNTIME_FUNCTION(Runtime_ObjectAssignTryFastcase) {
3920  HandleScope scope(isolate);
3921  DCHECK_EQ(2, args.length());
3922  auto source = Cast<JSReceiver>(args.at(0));
3923  auto target = Cast<JSReceiver>(args.at(1));
3924  DCHECK(IsJSObject(*source));
3925  DCHECK(IsJSObject(*target));
3926 
3927  Handle<Map> source_map = handle(source->map(), isolate);
3928  Handle<Map> target_map = handle(target->map(), isolate);
3929 
3930  DCHECK_EQ(target_map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors(), 0);
3931  DCHECK(!source_map->is_dictionary_map());
3932  DCHECK(!target_map->is_dictionary_map());
3933  DCHECK(!source_map->is_deprecated());
3934  DCHECK(!target_map->is_deprecated());
3935  DCHECK(target_map->is_extensible());
3936  DCHECK(!IsUndefined(*source, isolate) && !IsNull(*source, isolate));
3937  DCHECK(source_map->BelongsToSameNativeContextAs(isolate->context()));
3938 
3939  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
3940  {
3941  Tagged<Object> maybe_clone_target =
3942  GetCloneTargetMap<SideStepTransition::Kind::kObjectAssign>(
3943  isolate, source_map, target_map);
3944  if (maybe_clone_target == SideStepTransition::Unreachable) {
3945  return roots.undefined_value();
3946  } else if (maybe_clone_target != SideStepTransition::Empty) {
3947  return Cast<Map>(maybe_clone_target.GetHeapObject());
3948  }
3949  }
3950 
3951  auto UpdateCache = [&](Handle<Map> clone_target_map) {
3952  if (CanCacheCloneTargetMapTransition(source_map, clone_target_map, false,
3953  isolate)) {
3954  SetCloneTargetMap<SideStepTransition::Kind::kObjectAssign>(
3955  isolate, source_map, clone_target_map, target_map);
3956  }
3957  };
3958  auto UpdateCacheNotClonable = [&]() {
3959  if (CanCacheCloneTargetMapTransition(source_map, {}, false, isolate)) {
3960  SetCloneTargetMapUnsupported<SideStepTransition::Kind::kObjectAssign>(
3961  isolate, source_map, target_map);
3962  }
3963  };
3964 
3965  // In case we are still slack tracking let's defer a decision. The fast case
3966  // does not support it.
3967  if (source_map->IsInobjectSlackTrackingInProgress() ||
3968  target_map->IsInobjectSlackTrackingInProgress()) {
3969  return roots.undefined_value();
3970  }
3971 
3972  if (MaybeCanCloneObjectForObjectAssign(source, source_map, target, isolate)) {
3973  CHECK(target->map()->OnlyHasSimpleProperties());
3974  Maybe<bool> res = JSReceiver::SetOrCopyDataProperties(
3975  isolate, target, source, PropertiesEnumerationMode::kEnumerationOrder);
3976  DCHECK(res.FromJust());
3977  USE(res);
3978  Handle<Map> clone_target_map = handle(target->map(), isolate);
3979  if (clone_target_map->IsInobjectSlackTrackingInProgress()) {
3980  return roots.true_value();
3981  }
3982  if (CanFastCloneObjectToObjectLiteral(source_map, clone_target_map,
3983  target_map, false, isolate)) {
3984  CHECK(target->map()->OnlyHasSimpleProperties());
3985  UpdateCache(clone_target_map);
3986  } else {
3987  UpdateCacheNotClonable();
3988  }
3989  // We already did the copying here. Thus, returning true to cause the
3990  // CSA builtin to skip assigning anything.
3991  return roots.true_value();
3992  }
3993  UpdateCacheNotClonable();
3994  return roots.undefined_value();
3995 }

3997 /**
3998  * Loads a property with an interceptor performing post interceptor
3999  * lookup if interceptor failed.
4000  */
4001 RUNTIME_FUNCTION(Runtime_LoadPropertyWithInterceptor) {
4002  HandleScope scope(isolate);
4003  DCHECK_EQ(5, args.length());
4004  DirectHandle<Name> name = args.at<Name>(0);
4005  DirectHandle<Object> receiver_arg = args.at(1);
4006  Handle<JSObject> holder = args.at<JSObject>(2);
4007 
4008  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver;
4009  if (!TryCast<JSReceiver>(receiver_arg, &receiver)) {
4010  ASSIGN_RETURN_FAILURE_ON_EXCEPTION(
4011  isolate, receiver, Object::ConvertReceiver(isolate, receiver_arg));
4012  }
4013 
4014  {
4015  DirectHandle<InterceptorInfo> interceptor(holder->GetNamedInterceptor(),
4016  isolate);
4017  PropertyCallbackArguments arguments(isolate, interceptor->data(), *receiver,
4018  *holder, Just(kDontThrow));
4019 
4020  DirectHandle<Object> result = arguments.CallNamedGetter(interceptor, name);
4021  // An exception was thrown in the interceptor. Propagate.
4022  RETURN_FAILURE_IF_EXCEPTION_DETECTOR(isolate, arguments);
4023 
4024  if (!result.is_null()) {
4025  arguments.AcceptSideEffects();
4026  return *result;
4027  }
4028  // If the interceptor didn't handle the request, then there must be no
4029  // side effects.
4030  }
4031 
4032  LookupIterator it(isolate, receiver, name, holder);
4033  // Skip any lookup work until we hit the (possibly non-masking) interceptor.
4034  while (it.state() != LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR ||
4035  !it.GetHolder<JSObject>().is_identical_to(holder)) {
4036  DCHECK(it.state() != LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK || it.HasAccess());
4037  it.Next();
4038  }
4039  // Skip past the interceptor.
4040  it.Next();
4041  DirectHandle<Object> result;
4042  ASSIGN_RETURN_FAILURE_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, result, Object::GetProperty(&it));
4043 
4044  if (it.IsFound()) return *result;
4045 
4046  int slot = args.tagged_index_value_at(3);
4047  DirectHandle<FeedbackVector> vector = args.at<FeedbackVector>(4);
4048  FeedbackSlot vector_slot = FeedbackVector::ToSlot(slot);
4049  FeedbackSlotKind slot_kind = vector->GetKind(vector_slot);
4050  // It could actually be any kind of load IC slot here but the predicate
4051  // handles all the cases properly.
4052  if (!LoadIC::ShouldThrowReferenceError(slot_kind)) {
4053  return ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).undefined_value();
4054  }
4055 
4056  // Throw a reference error.
4057  THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_FAILURE(
4058  isolate, NewReferenceError(MessageTemplate::kNotDefined, it.name()));
4059 }

4061 RUNTIME_FUNCTION(Runtime_StorePropertyWithInterceptor) {
4062  HandleScope scope(isolate);
4063  DCHECK_EQ(3, args.length());
4064  // Runtime functions don't follow the IC's calling convention.
4065  DirectHandle<Object> value = args.at(0);
4066  DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver = args.at<JSObject>(1);
4067  DirectHandle<Name> name = args.at<Name>(2);
4068 
4069  // TODO(ishell): Cache interceptor_holder in the store handler like we do
4070  // for LoadHandler::kInterceptor case.
4071  DirectHandle<JSObject> interceptor_holder = receiver;
4072  if (IsJSGlobalProxy(*receiver) &&
4073  (!receiver->HasNamedInterceptor() ||
4074  receiver->GetNamedInterceptor()->non_masking())) {
4075  interceptor_holder =
4076  direct_handle(Cast<JSObject>(receiver->map()->prototype()), isolate);
4077  }
4078  DCHECK(interceptor_holder->HasNamedInterceptor());
4079  {
4080  DirectHandle<InterceptorInfo> interceptor(
4081  interceptor_holder->GetNamedInterceptor(), isolate);
4082 
4083  DCHECK(!interceptor->non_masking());
4084  // TODO(ishell, 348688196): why is it known that it shouldn't throw?
4085  Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw = Just(kDontThrow);
4086  PropertyCallbackArguments callback_args(isolate, interceptor->data(),
4087  *receiver, *receiver, should_throw);
4088 
4089  v8::Intercepted intercepted =
4090  callback_args.CallNamedSetter(interceptor, name, value);
4091  // Stores initiated by StoreICs don't care about the exact result of
4092  // the store operation returned by the callback as long as it doesn't
4093  // throw an exception.
4094  constexpr bool ignore_return_value = true;
4095  InterceptorResult result;
4096  MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_FAILURE_ON_EXCEPTION(
4097  isolate, result,
4098  callback_args.GetBooleanReturnValue(intercepted, "Setter",
4099  ignore_return_value));
4100 
4101  switch (result) {
4102  case InterceptorResult::kFalse:
4103  case InterceptorResult::kTrue:
4104  return *value;
4105 
4106  case InterceptorResult::kNotIntercepted:
4107  // Proceed storing past the interceptor.
4108  break;
4109  }
4110  }
4111 
4112  LookupIterator it(isolate, receiver, name, receiver);
4113  // Skip past any access check on the receiver.
4114  while (it.state() == LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK) {
4115  DCHECK(it.HasAccess());
4116  it.Next();
4117  }
4118  // Skip past the interceptor on the receiver.
4119  DCHECK_EQ(LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR, it.state());
4120  it.Next();
4121 
4122  MAYBE_RETURN(Object::SetProperty(&it, value, StoreOrigin::kNamed),
4123  ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).exception());
4124  return *value;
4125 }
